title: venison stew
directions: Combine carrots, potatoes, venison, consomme, salt, onion flakes, celery and mushrooms in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together Bisquick mix, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Over this, pour peaches.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch baking dish in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: munchie peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together the peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Place in microwave oven and cook 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to the syrup mixture, blending well.
Return dish to oven.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup will be very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Use an airtight container to store the candy.
Yield:
Approximately 1 pound.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well with table fork. Add shortening and mix with fork until ingredients are crumbly. In a small bowl, beat together with fork 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions and, with hands, shape each portion in a flat round patty, ready for rolling.
Wrap each in plastic wrap and chill at least 1/2 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten each cookie with a small glass dipped into sugar; place 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes before removing.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: never fail lemon pie
directions: When stiff peaks form, add to pie top.
Bake in 400° oven until meringue starts to brown, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: peggy's meatball subs
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, egg and breadcrumbs and mix well.
Chop medium onion and red pepper; add to mixture along with minced garlic and seasoning.
Crumble beef over mixture; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place in a single layer in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is no longer pink; turn once while baking.
Drain off fat and transfer to a large saucepan; add remaining spaghetti sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Spoon meatballs and sauce onto 1/2 of each bun.
Top with peppers, olives, Parmesan cheese and sliced red onions if desired.
Servings: 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze a 10 ounce package of chopped spinach until dry.
Stir together spinach and next 5 ingredients.
Blend well. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Serve in hollowed out round bread with any type of veggie.
Cut bread into cubes and serve with dip.

title: amish cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour.
Add flour and mix well.
Roll in small balls or drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Press flat.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Let set.
Mix remaining ingredients together in large bowl.
Add date mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine soup and cheese over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Add the cooked, cubed chicken and parsley.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Serve over the spaghetti.

title: broccoli rice medley
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mary gregory's sweet cabbage salad
directions: Prepare vegetables and fruits.
Place in a large bowl and toss with lemon, mayo and caraway seed.
Chill and then serve. Yields 2 portions only.

title: cranberry ripple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In large bowl beat margarine, sugar, eggs and extract.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to beaten mixture, beating at low speed until smooth. Spread half batter into pan.
Spoon 1/2 cup cranberry sauce over batter.
Spoon remaining batter over sauce, spreading out as much as possible.
Dot with remaining cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Makes 1 ring.

title: frozen dessert
directions: In double boiler, melt marshmallows in milk, cook, add whipped cream.
Cover bottom of 8 x 10-inch dish with cookie crumbs. Layer marshmallow mix and crumbs ending with crumbs.
Freeze.

title: gingered chicken bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and coat chicken.
In pan brown chicken in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Remove to 2 quart casserole.
Add remaining margarine to pan and brown potatoes and onion.
Stir in reserved flour then water.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in beans.

title: sour cream blueberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine the biscuit mix and 3/4 cup sugar.
In another bowl, combine the eggs and sour cream; stir into the dry ingredients just until combined.
Fold in the blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups three-fourths full.
Sprinkle with the remaining sugar.

title: mull cider
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil, then reduce heat to keep warm. Serves 12.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook the grits.
Add the garlic cheese cut into pieces.
Add the butter; stir until melted.
Add 2 beaten eggs with enough milk to make 1 cup. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry ice(to serve with turkey dinner)
directions: Boil cranberries and water until skins pop.
Strain through sieve.
Add 2 cups sugar to each quart juice.
Return to heat until sugar dissolves.
Add juice of 1 lemon to each pint juice. Put in freezer.

title: peanut, bacon, corn muffins
directions: Mix meal, sugar and peanut butter.
In another bowl, mix rest of ingredients.
Add to first mixture, then put into a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: indian wedding cake and icing
directions: Stir ingredients with spoon.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: briar patch bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce and onion and heat.
Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package, except using 1/2 cup milk.
Layer half of macaroni in a baking dish; cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining macaroni. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(You can just mix all together and bake instead of layering.)

title: soup dip
directions: Place in a saucepan
(careful not to burn) and mix both ingredients over a low
heat
until they are mixed well.
This is great on a cold day.

title: hot clam dip
directions: In saucepan, simmer clams and lemon juice for 15 minutes.
In another saucepan, simmer onion, garlic, pepper, parsley, butter, oregano, Tabasco and cayenne until soft.
Combine two mixtures. Stir in bread crumbs.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Top with crumbled cheese.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese; dust with paprika. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; 45 minutes if frozen.

title: veronica's green beans spanish style
directions: Cook beans (1-inch pieces) in water for 10 minutes (canned beans need no precooking).
Drain.
Heat garlic in olive oil until brown, then discard.
Add pimentos to oil; stir.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Add beans, cover and cook for 5 minutes (or until tender) over low heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a heavy skillet until meat is browned.
Stir in seasonings, potato and tomatoes.
Add frozen peas and water.
Cover tightly; cook on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, or until potatoes and peas are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
This dish should be moist, but not soupy.

title: name unknown bars
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Press 2/3 of the mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate chips, milk and butter.
Put over the crust and cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: super spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large roaster on the range, fry the minced garlic in the olive oil.
Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato puree. Stir while simmering.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Add seasonings and whole onions.
Place roaster in oven and bake for approximately 6 hours or until onions are cooked.
Stir occasionally and add approximately 1/4 cup water.

title: mustard pickle
directions: Place in weak salt water and let soak overnight.
The next morning, cook in same water.
Drain.
Add cucumbers.
Mix with dressing.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Boil water, coffee and sugar for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool completely, then add vodka and vanilla. Pour into bottles.
Best if kept for 6 weeks in refrigerator in sealed bottles.
Share with friends.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cinnamon and 1 teaspoon sugar) together.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Blend all together and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until well done, about 35 to 40 minutes, when middle does not shake.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit.
Mix Dream Whip.
Do not add vanilla.
Fold Dream Whip into fruit gently.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours. Serve as dessert or salad.

title: turnips and pork chops
directions: Clean and wash pork chops; cut into pieces. Put cooking oil, pork chops, salt and pepper and onions in pot. Smother down until pork chops and onions are brown. Then put in turnips and stir to mix well.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple (with juice) and pudding.
Add marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well and chill.

title: microwave texas trash
directions: In a flat microwavable dish place butter, Worcestershire sauce, and salt.
Microwave on high for 1 minute, or until butter is melted. Stir well.
Add cereals, nuts, bugles and pretzels, mixing thoroughly to coat.
Microwave on high for 3 minutes. Stir.
Microwave on high 3 additional minutes. Let cool and enjoy.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon in an iron skillet at medium-high heat until crispy. Remove from heat, drain and blot bacon with paper towel.
Wipe grease with paper towel after pouring out of skillet.
Then at medium-high heat, put okra in skillet and cook until okra starts to lightly brown, stirring constantly; then add the bacon and tomatoes with liquid.
Cook at medium-low until okra is tender.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Mixture will thicken.

title: sweet potato sausage casserole
directions: Mix sausage, Raisin Bran and 1/2 cup milk.
Place mixture on bottom of 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine potatoes, remaining milk, salt, nutmeg and ginger.
Spread over sausage in casserole. Place apple rings on top of potatoes, pressing slightly.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and additional nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: herb salmon bake
directions: Place 1 cup of the Croutettes in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole or 8 x 8-inch baking dish; sprinkle with 1 cup of the salmon and 1 cup cheese.
Repeat, using remaining Croutettes, salmon and cheese.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in milk, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Pour over contents of baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Garnish with parsley, pimiento strips or pepper rings, if desired.
Serve immediately. Yield: 6 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Cook beans and mash along with juice.
Mix all together, beating well.
Pour into crust and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300 degrees.

title: old-fashioned peach preserves
directions: Combine fruit and sugar; let stand 12 to 18 hours in a cool place.
Bring slowly to boiling, stirring frequently.
Boil gently until fruit becomes clear and syrup thick, about 40 minutes.
As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Skim if necessary.
Pour boiling hot preserves into jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into shell.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy. Gradually, add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Bake until meringue is golden brown.
Cool and chill before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers and margarine. Pour into baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Melt margarine, and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan(low-fat)
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in beaten eggs, then into crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour, until fork-tender, at 375°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, onion, green pepper, soft bread crumbs and tomato sauce and press into unbaked pie crust.
Top with cheese, egg, Worcestershire sauce, milk and mustard.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: its wild rice
directions: Put a layer of each in a pan; cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Do not look until time is up.
This recipe does not call for wild rice.

title: mei fun noodles
directions: Soak noodles in a bowl filled halfway with water for five minutes.
In a big pan (preferably a wok), stir-fry garlic and onion.
Then add shrimp, pork, cabbage, carrots and a dash of salt and pepper.
Stir for about 1 to 2 minutes and then add 1/2 cup of water.
Wait until the water is boiling, then add the noodles and mix.
Also add 1 tablespoon of soy sauce for coloring.
Serves 4.

title: tacos for 4
directions: In frying pan, saute meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Fill taco shells with meat.
Prepare topping and serve in separate bowls.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Beat eggs and cream with seasonings.
Use pepper and salt to taste.
Place crumbled bacon or ham on top of pie crust with cheese slices on top.
Pour egg and cream mixture over this and bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat with pepperoni and mushrooms.
Then add spaghetti sauce.
Next, cook noodles and then drain.
Combine noodles and the meat sauce mixture.
Top with cheese and bake in 13 x 9 pan at 350° until cheese melts and sauce bubbles.

title: homemade bread
directions: Bring to simmer the milk, 1 cup water, 2/3 cup sugar, margarine and salt.
Pour into large bowl and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add eggs to lukewarm mixture.
Then begin to add flour.
I always put in 6 cups and beat with electric mixer.
Then I add the other 6 cups and mix with my hands.
Place on well floured board and knead 10 minutes.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.

title: chili sauce dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or tortilla chips.

title: fast and easy casserole
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet; drain.
Push meat to 1 side and saute onion.
Add remaining ingredients except olives.
Season to taste.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with olives.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and cool, not set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in jello mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter reese's cups
directions: Mix butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Press in sheet pan.
Melt Hershey bars and spread on top.
Chill.
Break into small pieces and store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is thick.
Sift dry ingredients together; fold into egg mixture.
Turn onto shallow pan lined with waxed paper.
Use a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for approximately 13 minutes at 425°. Cut edges off cake; turn onto a clean cloth.
Remove waxed paper. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Spread cake with jelly or other fillings.
Starting with small end, roll cake; wrap in clean towel and let cool.

title: lemonade cake with glaze
directions: Beat together the first 5 ingredients.
Bake in 13-inch oblong pan greased and floured in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar and yeast.
Add 3 cups flour, eggs and oil, then add another 3 cups flour.
Mix well and let rise to double in size, covered, in a warm place.
Ready to use when it has doubled in size.
Make into rolls; let rise again and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix while hot all ingredients.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: martha baker's strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking
pan.
Sprinkle evenly 1 cup of marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Combine the strawberries in syrup, completely thawed, with jello and set aside.

title: florida citrus salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until serving time.

title: trees and raisins salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion in a large bowl. Blend together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Stir to coat well.
Cover and marinate at least 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: lucky if anything is left
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together for crust.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk, then layer. Put one Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: stir-fry steak strips with pepper and onions
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, add flank strips and stir-fry 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until lightly browned.
(Meat will be rare.) With a slotted spoon, lift meat to a plate.
Add remaining tablespoon olive oil to skillet.
When oil is hot, add bell pepper, onions and garlic.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in V-8 juice, Worcestershire sauce, thyme and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes to develop flavor. Return steak strips to skillet and cook, stirring 1 minute longer to heat meat.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add Ragu sauce and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces each. Place in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour sauce over this.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole with praline topping
directions: Mix until well blended the first 7 ingredients.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a shallow baking pan.
Beat eggs in a large bowl. Stir in potatoes until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread evenly in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and nuts in a medium-size bowl.
Work in butter with hands until well blended. Sprinkle on potato mixture evenly.
Bake for 60 or 70 minutes, until topping is browned and bubbling.
Makes 12 servings.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and vanilla.
Chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll a teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Grease bottom of a glass with margarine.
Dip glass in sugar and use to flatten ball of dough.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: mom keehn's homemade baked beans
directions: Pick over dried beans to remove stones and soak in cold water overnight or at least a few hours.
This cuts cooking time.
Drain and cover with fresh water.
Add salt and dried onion and boil slowly (careful they don't boil dry).
Taste one in about 1/2 hour and each 10 minutes thereafter until bean is just tender, but not mushy.
Water should be boiled to about 2/3.

title: spinach fandango
directions: Thaw the spinach and drain the excess water.
Chop if necessary.
Brown the meat and onion in a large skillet.
Add the spinach, soup, mushrooms, rice, sour cream, garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover the casserole with thick slices of Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel apricot grunt
directions: In a saucepan, combine apricots and tapioca; let stand for 15 minutes. Add brown sugar, margarine and lemon juice. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil. Reduce heat to low, keep warm. To make dumplings, combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl; cut in margarine until crumbly. Add milk; mix just until combined. Pour warm fruit mixture into an ungreased 2 qt. baking dish (mixture will be very thick). Drop the batter into 6 mounds onto fruit mixture. Cover and bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into a dumpling comes out clean (do not lift cover while baking). In a saucepan, bring brown sugar and water to a boil; cook until sugar is dissolved. Spoon over dumplings; bake uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Serve with cream if desired.

title: apple cake with butter sauce
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Sift together the salt, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda.
Combine together with the apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with Butter Sauce and whipped cream.

title: egg brunch
directions: Mix eggs, salt, milk, dry mustard and 2/3 of the crumbled bacon in bowl.
Alternate layers of bread cubes, cheese cubes and egg mixture in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, put 1/2 of the crumbled bacon on top and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 12.
Great for Christmas morning!

title: cornbread(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch square pan prepared with Pam spray and flour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: southern burgers
directions: Combine in skillet and simmer on low for about 1/2 hour.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours.
Form into ball and roll into parsley flakes.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Drain and thaw broccoli.
Combine cornbread mix, eggs and butter.
Add broccoli and bake in cupcake pan as package directs.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift together flour and spice.
Add to pumpkin mixture with water.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy rolls
directions: Scald milk.
While cooling, add sugar, yeast and enough flour to make a batter.
Let rise about 2 1/2 hours.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out on lightly floured board; cut like biscuits.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt oleo and cheese together and mix with remaining ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Very rich.

title: mushroom sauce green beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions. Add the soup and 1/2 can Durkee onions. Stir.
Put remaining onions on top and bake in oven for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 13 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° until begins to brown.

title: granny's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones; dice.
Place butter in deep frying pan. Add the flour.
Brown slightly, then add 2 cups chicken broth, vegetables and cream. Cook on slow heat until vegetables are done. Stir in diced chicken. Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in pie crust; place in oven at 375° or 400° until crust is browned.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together very good and bake at 350° until done.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: german fried vegetables
directions: Toss all vegetables with equal amount of flour and meal.
Fry as you would fry okra, using half shortening and half butter.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil and sugar and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and add dressing.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars and butter or shortening. Stir until shortening is melted.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa; add to oatmeal mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add about half package of chips and mix together.

title: horsey sauce
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve cold on sliced tomatoes, baked ham, boiled shrimp, baked chicken or any broiled steak.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Blend all ingredients (except chocolate chips).
Then put it out into an ungreased cookie sheet.
Make sure it's as flat as possible.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Shake one 12 ounce package of chocolate chips out evenly across the surface.
Return to the oven for a few minutes to melt the chips.
Remove and spread chips around with a table knife.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, 1/2 cup.
Add sugar and shortening to milk.
Then add 5 cups flour to make batter (it will be like pancake batter).
Set in warm place to rise until doubled. After doubled in size, add 1 teaspoon soda, 2 1/2 teaspoons salt and 2 teaspoons baking powder.
Add enough flour to make dough (2 1/2 cups).
Roll out on floured board and cut in 1-inch thick biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen, put in Ziploc bags.
Take out and thaw; let rise when needed.
Cook at 350°.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese on low speed.
Beat in confectioners sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust. Freeze until ready to serve.
Set out a little time ahead of serving to let it soften a bit.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Boil butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans.
Spread over graham crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Spread pumpkin filling over uncooked batter; bake 10 minutes in 450° oven.
When cake is cooled, serve topped with whipped cream.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar slowly.
Add flour, chopped nuts and flavoring.
Roll dough into long rolls on board covered with powdered sugar (may need a little flour).
Chill rolls.
When well chilled (or overnight), slice thick, at least 1/2-inch and bake on cookie sheets about 15 minutes at 350°.
When done, sprinkle well with powdered sugar.

title: tangy german potato frank salad
directions: In skillet, combine celery soup, dry milk powder, sweet pickle relish, vinegar, onion, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup water; bring
to boiling.
Reduce
heat.
Stir in cubed potatoes and sliced frankfurters;
simmer about 10 minutes or until heated through. Garnish
with
snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil rice according to directions and drain.
Combine all ingredients in bowl or pot except bread crumbs and cheese for topping.
Mix until cheese is stringy.
Sprinkle bread crumbs in a greased 8-inch pie pan.
Add ingredients to pie plate.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Put in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: grilled peppers
directions: Place pepper pieces on metal skewers, alternating colors. Brush peppers with oil. Cook on grill for 10 minutes, turning frequently.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce jam cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat well after each egg.
Add jam.
Sift all dry ingredients together; sift several times.
Add a little to nuts and raisins.
Add to dry ingredients, then add to butter mixture, then applesauce and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use your favorite icing.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed, but decrease water by 1/2 cup.
Add cream cheese while jello mixture is still warm and crush with fork.
Drain pineapple and add to jello.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and chill.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peanuts in saucepan.
Cook and stir to fast rolling boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring, allowing to boil more slowly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, add peanuts and beat until candy starts to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Yield: 24 clusters.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously prick bottom and sides of pie crust with fork.
Bake 10 minutes; remove from oven.
In large bowl, beat eggs; stir in sugar and butter.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chips and nuts.
Pour into pie crust; return to oven.
Bake additional 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set (pie will not test done in center).
Serve warm or cool with ice cream; drizzle with topping. Garnish with Kisses.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: david rossi's marinade
directions: Mix well. Good on pork or chicken.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Spread berries in a greased pan.
Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar; add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Spread batter over berries.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch together.
Sift over batter.
Pour boiling water over.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: beef roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with steak sauce and add dry onion soup.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Wrap in tinfoil and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all of the ingredients except for the tomato sauce and mix lightly, then add sauce and mix well. Shape loaf and spread ketchup lightly over the top. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil the potatoes until done.
Chop celery, olives and onions.
Add pinch of oregano, teaspoon of mustard and the 4 boiled eggs (chopped) to celery, olives and onions.
Add mayonnaise and relish to mixture.
Set small bowl of potatoes to side.
Add ingredients to other potatoes and stir well.
Mash small bowl of potatoes until smooth and add to mixture.
Stir well.
Sprinkle paprika over potato salad.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: crab salad spread
directions: Cook cream cheese, soup and gelatin over medium heat until creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add crab, onion and celery.
Place in jello mold and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: veggie bars
directions: Lay crescent rolls out on cookie sheet.
Bake as directed. Cool.
Mix all ingredients, except for vegetables and cheese. Spread mixture on baked crust.
Top with raw chopped vegetables and then add cheese.
Refrigerate at least two hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: apple-pecan cobbler
directions: Place sliced apples in a greased 8-inch round baking dish. In another bowl mix together 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 of the pecans; sprinkle this mixture over the apples in the baking dish.
Stir together remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.

title: italian chicken and potatoes
directions: In large casserole dish, pour Italian dressing to cover bottom of dish (1/4 cup).	Sprinkle 1/2 minced garlic in dish. Add chicken.
Pour remaining dressing over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining garlic over chicken.
Slice potatoes around chicken; stir
potatoes during baking time to coat.	Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown.

title: citrus cooler
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring sugar until it dissolves.
Cover; remove from heat and let set until cool.
Strain.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, fill glasses with equal amounts of juice, water and ginger ale. Add ice.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish previously greased.
Scatter the chicken over and top with soup mixture.
Sprinkle with grated medium Cheddar.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, honey, milk and lemon peel.
Serve with fruit; refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix in the remaining ingredients, folding apples in carefully.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes in a well-greased 8-inch pie plate.

title: crab stuffed shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel, clean and split shrimp down the back to butterfly.
Combine butter, crab, onion and parsley in a small pan.
Heat until onion is limp.
Add enough breadcrumbs just to bind the stuffing.
Dip shrimp in egg and then in additional crumbs and place on a baking sheet.
Stuff each shrimp with the crab stuffing.
Bake 15 minutes, until shrimp flesh is opaque. Serves 2 to 3.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake until brown at 450°, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water and cool.
Add sherbet and fruit.
Chill until set.
Serves 8.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Yields 6 cups.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Rinse and dry vegetables.
Slice squash and eggplant about 1/2-inch thick.
Halve tomatoes lengthwise.
Cut peppers into strips.
Rub vegetables with olive oil and lightly salt and pepper.
Grill about 3 minutes on each side or until desired doneness.

title: new year's nonalcoholic drinks
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to boil, stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil gently 5 minutes.
Makes 2 cups. Keeps 6 months in refrigerator.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except carrots, in saucepan.
Mix well and
bring
to a boil.
Pour over carrots and cool.
May keep, covered,
in refrigerator.
Should set overnight before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well. Saute onion and celery in butter. Add cheese to hot mixture to melt. Combine with all other ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together well in one bowl.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sin pudding
directions: First Layer (crust):
Mix flour, 3 to 4 tablespoons sugar, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts and press into an 11 x 7 1/2-inch Pyrex pan.
Preheat oven to 350°; cook 10 minutes at 300°.

title: crescent italians
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add the next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish; top with cheese.
Have rolls prepared or keep casserole hot while preparing them.

title: grilled lamb chops
directions: Marinate chops in dressing 2 to 8 hours in the refrigerator. Cook on hot grill for approximately 5 to 7 minutes on each side.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine and mix all the liquids.
Stir in dry ingredients. Add nuts and dates.
Pour mixture into 3 large greased loaf pans. Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: salmon puff
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until mixture appears set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: grandma's applesauce cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and cloves together.
Set aside.
Mix in a large bowl the shortening, sugar, egg, vanilla and applesauce.
Blend thoroughly.
Add optional raisins and stir.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture and blend. Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 11 minutes. Moist and delicious cookies.

title: white squash custard
directions: Cook squash
until
tender
enough to mash.
Add sugar, lemon flavor, vanilla, eggs, flour, margarine and milk.
Blend together well.
Pour into
unbaked
pie shell.
This is enough for 3 pies. Bake at 350°
for
to 40 minutes.
Use 9-inch pie pan.

title: cherry freeze
directions: Mix well; freeze.
Good several weeks in freezer.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients, form into hamburger shaped patties.
Fry in frying pan.

title: easy ice cream pie
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, stir together corn syrup and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated. Press mixture into pie pan to form pie crust.
Fill crust with softened ice cream.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: baked zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Wash
zucchini;
do
not
peel unless the skin is tough. Peel tomatoes
and
onion.
Slice all into very thin crosswise slices. In	a
greased
baking
dish, make alternate layers of zucchini, tomatoes
and
onions,
sprinkling each layer with a little
salt and
pepper,
dotting with butter.	Cover the top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until vegetables are tender.

title: canine cookies(bacon)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn oven off but let sit in warm oven 10 minutes longer to dry with oven door shut.
No preservatives, so store in refrigerator.
May substitute whole wheat flour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until it falls off bone.
Skin and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in small pieces.
Cook broccoli.
Place broccoli over top of chicken.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: *Rinse well.
Cut up in bite size pieces.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple and cherry pie filling in flat cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter over this and top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy anadama bread
directions: In large bowl, combine cornmeal, 1 cup of the flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
In saucepan, heat water, molasses, butter, fennel and anise seed to 120°.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Beat in egg and 1 cup of the flour.
Then add last cup of flour.
Knead lightly.
Put in two small bread pans or one regular size pan. Put in warm place and let rise until doubled.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until it forms hard ball when tested in water.
Add peanuts and cook until caramelized.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla, margarine and soda.
Stir until frothy.
Pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Don't touch after pouring until cold.
Break into pieces.

title: chocolate cherry cordials
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, confectioners sugar and flavorings. If mixture is too soft, add additional sugar. Mold just enough around each cherry to completely cover. Place on waxed paper lined tray.
Cover and chill. Remove 1/3 of the cherries from the refrigerator 15 minutes before dipping. Keep remaining centers chilled.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all together; roll in small balls.
Press out with thumb. Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown the rice, celery and onion in butter.
Add tomatoes. Sprinkle top with grated cheese; add buttered bread crumbs and bake until brown.

title: pepper sandwiches
directions: All ingredients should be chopped fine or ground.
Moisten with mayonnaise and spread between thin slices of white bread.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, butter and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, over medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer or to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; let stand for 15 minutes. Do not stir.
Add vanilla and beat for eight to 10 minutes or until mixture begins to lose gloss. Stir in cherries if desired and nuts.
Quickly pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Rum or brandy flavor can be substituted for vanilla.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: quick salad
directions: Combine all three ingredients.

title: party potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, chives and garlic powder.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve immediately.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: slushy punch
directions: Add Jell-O
to	hot water and mix well. Add sugar.
Mix together.
Let
cool.
Add	ReaLemon and pineapple juice.
Mix well
and
freeze
in
plastic container or Ziploc bags.
When ready to serve, let thaw to a slush and add 2 quarts of ginger ale.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together into a bowl.
Mix well, then chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Combine beef and milk.
Divide into 5 patties; place on waxed paper and form into 6-inch circles.
Place dressing in center of each.
Draw meat up around dressing to form a ball.
Place in 1 1/4-quart casserole and pour following mixture over meat.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and spices together.
Add to oil mixture.
Add flour and mix good.
Add pecans, raisins and pears.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan or 3 small loaf pans.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes with enough water to cover. Add bouillon.
When potatoes are cooked, add milk and butter.
Use flour to thicken to desired consistency.
Pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbled.
Drain excess grease.

title: oven pork chops
directions: In a large cake pan or casserole dish, spread potatoes.
Spoon soup over potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Then spread cheese over soup if you like.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Cut pepper and onion and mix with cabbage. Heat to boiling point the vinegar, sugar, oil, honey and salt. Watch when this comes to a boil, it could boil over easily.
Pour hot mixture over slaw.
Cool and refrigerate.
Will keep for two weeks or more.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in uncovered casserole dish.

title: colorado broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish; season with garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Add broccoli; mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 can milk (soup can).
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Slice Cheddar cheese to cover.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil after 45 minutes to allow cheese to brown.

title: layer fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add baking powder to flour and sift.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk. Beat egg whites and stir into mixture only long enough to mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: economical cream cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating well, then add vanilla, milk and flour; beat well.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Bake in moderate oven.
Use your favorite icing.

title: piney creek sausage bake
directions: Cook sausage, drain and crumble. Layer in an ungreased 9 x 12 inch pan. Sausage, then hash brown, followed by cheddar. Beat eggs with milk, salt & pepper. Sprinkle with parmesan, then paprika.

title: seven day slaw
directions: Pour 1 cup sugar over first three ingredients and let set while you bring to a boil remaining ingredients.
Pour immediately over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: avocado salad
directions: Peel avocados and cut into cubes.
Slice onion paper thin and separate into rings.
Place together in a bowl.
Mix oil, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for several hours, stirring mixture occasionally. Just before serving, peel and section orange.
Add to salad and toss lightly.
Serve over a bed of lettuce.

title: party cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla; add soda and salt to flour.
Stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's (reserve remaining M&M's for decorating).
Drop by teaspoon into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain fat. Spray a 9 x 15-inch pan with Pam. Place crescent rolls on the bottom to make a crust.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over top of crescent rolls.
Mix together eggs and milk and pour over top.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: gooey snickers brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter and evaporated milk. Beat on low speed until well blended (1 to 2 minutes). Spread half of batter into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and place candy bar slices evenly over surface. Drop remaining half of batter by spoonful over candy bars as evenly as possible. Place back in oven and bake for 20 minutes (brownies will jiggle slightly on top when you remove them). Let cool; cut into bars.

title: hot ham barbecues
directions: Heat onion and celery in butter.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boiling point and let simmer about 1 1/2 hours.

title: zesty french bread
directions: Brush cut side with dressing.
Top with cheese and basil. Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut into 2-inch slices.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar together and press lightly in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix with Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar with mixer.
Put on top of pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello in water; mix in strawberries.
After it sets up, pour over creamed cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: sweet kosher dillies
directions: Slice dills real thin, put back in jar.
Mix all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over dill slices and onion slices in jar.
Let set 24 hours.

title: apple pie with candied crust
directions: Place apples in well-greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Put in a large saucepan the sugar and molasses; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Let cool.
Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves. Dissolve baking soda in cold coffee.
Beat eggs; mix all the ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: snow ball dip
directions: Cut off top of bread; set aside.

title: crackling bread
directions: Sift cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt into large bowl.
Add cracklings, buttermilk, eggs and bacon drippings.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Pound your chicken breasts out before starting.
This will make them more tender.
Place ham on one side and cheese on the other of uncooked chicken breasts.
After doing this, drop into bread crumbs; coat both sides of your Cordon Blue.
In a skillet, add butter, onion and garlic powder.
Place your chicken in hot skillet for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not burn.
Add white wine and let boil 1 minute.
Cover and place in oven for 40 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: oriental chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box, using broth from chicken for water.
Cook only 15 minutes if done.
Mix all ingredients; place in large casserole and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or freeze and then bake when needed.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove outer leaves of cabbage.
Drop into boiling water; parboil for 5 minutes or until soft.
Drain; trim out some of thick veins.
Combine beef, rice, parsley, egg, milk, 1/2 of onion, salt and pepper.
Place 1 spoonful of mixture on each cabbage leaf and roll up.
Place in casserole dish in which there is about 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix soup, water and brown sugar; pour over rolls.
Add bay leaves, cloves and remaining onion.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ding-a-lings
directions: Heat chips over hot water until melted.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Leave over hot water while spooning small amounts out on wax paper.
Great eating.

title: great omelette casserole
directions: Put 1/2 cup cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir cornmeal in the boiling water.
Cook until thick, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to cornmeal mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar into the strawberries, juice and all.
Add the eggs, nuts and oil.
Stir carefully, just enough to mix well.
Bake in well-greased loaf pans or coffee cans.
Makes three.
Can use square pans also. Bake for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Ragu and sour cream.
Cook noodles.
In baking dish, layer noodles, then ground beef.
Add cheese.
Put in oven to melt cheese.
Ready to serve.

title: edith's rave reviews cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.

title: swiss-style chuck roast
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving the juice. Place large piece of foil on a baking sheet. Place meat on foil; sprinkle with soup mix. Top with tomatoes and mushrooms.

title: peach preserves
directions: Peel peaches; cut in halves or quarters.
Boil sugar and water together until they are clear and the syrup is thick.
Put peaches in clean hot jars and fill jars to overflowing with boiling syrup.
Seal at once.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: You take a whole bunch of pieces of chicken and put them on your grill.
The grill has to be 10 degrees hot.
Be sure the chicken has bones in it.
Cook it for 5 minutes.
Take it off the grill and eat it.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix well.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet in rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sausage pie
directions: Place crumbled	cooked sausage in bottom of pie shells. Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over sausage.
Cook, uncovered, on
cookie
sheet
on
lowest shelf of oven at 350° until golden
brown,
about 55 minutes.
Serve at once or cool and freeze if desired.

title: good "vegie" salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables well.
Add the green pepper, celery and onion.

title: noah's ark clam chowder
directions: Saute the onion and clams in butter.
Mix the clam chowder, soup and half and half.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Bake in oven at 200° for 4 hours.
If too thick, add some clam juice.

title: apricot mold
directions: Heat crushed pineapple over medium heat.
Stir in jello until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Chill until it thickens.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill.
Turn into an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Serves 6.

title: taco tostitos dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and spread in bottom of a deep pie plate.
Place lettuce, onion, tomato and green pepper on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and orange rind; add juice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill again until mixture will mound.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges. Place in baking dish. Mix margarine with brown and white sugars and salt. Pour over potatoes. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peggy's brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift into mixture all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When done, push down with spatula.

title: kris kringle cake
directions: Combine spice cake mix, shortening and boiling water in large bowl.
Mix until well moistened.
Let stand for 30 minutes.

title: quick chocolate-nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour candy quickly into greased 9 x 5 or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool, then cut. Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 dozen pieces.

title: whipped cream biscuits
directions: Mix flour and cream until very blended.
Butter hands and form ping-pong sized balls.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Biscuits will double in size.
Can be frozen 1-inch apart.

title: california baked potatoes
directions: Toss potato spears with dressing. Place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with garlic powder and parsley. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until crispy.

title: tommy's strawberry pie
directions: Bake 2 pie shells (frozen), according to directions.
In pan mix 2 cups sugar, Jell-O and cornstarch.
Add 2 cups water and stir well.
Bring to boil and stir until thickens.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fill pie shells with sliced berries and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate until set well.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Knead a small amount at a time and roll out thinly.
Cut into halves.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: easy pie crust for cobblers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over fruit cobbler.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender or bake small turkey.
Remove from bone and cut in small pieces.
Saute onions, celery and green peppers until limp in margarine, but not brown.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain.
Add all other ingredients except cheese. Place half in large baking pan; add half of the cheese.
Place other half chicken mixture and rest of the cheese.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: apricot slush punch
directions: Boil 3 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and add 1 large can pineapple juice and 1 large frozen orange juice (undiluted).
Freeze in gallon jugs filling below the neck to allow for expansion.
Remove from freezer 2 to 3 hours before using.
Add 1 liter 7-Up to each recipe.
Makes 40 (15 ounce) servings.

title: heavenly banana delight
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix pudding, condensed milk and sweet milk together for 2 minutes, or until well blended.
Refrigerate 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sue's frosting
directions: Cream the shortening and softened butter in mixer.
Add sugar slowly. Add milk. Blend. Add vanilla. Add coloring now, if desired.

title: hot punch
directions: Fill 8 to 10-cup percolator basket with cinnamon sticks, sugar and spices.
Pour pineapple juice, water and cranberry juice through percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Set control on strong and complete perking process.
Hold on mild setting.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients and drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool a minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook eggs in butter without stirring until set. Remove from skillet; cut into strips. Keep warm.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chop in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour uncooked rice over pork chops.
Mix soup and milk and pour over rice until all is covered.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Delicious.

title: homemade irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender at low speed, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth and serve over ice if desired.
Store tightly covered in fridge up to one month.
Stir or shake before serving.

title: rouladen(doc bowen special)
directions: Cut meat into 2-inch strips.
Spread each piece with mustard, then a strip of bacon and sprinkle with chopped onion.
Roll into bundles and secure with 2 toothpicks.
Dredge in (or cover with) flour and brown in cooking oil.
A good brown crust adds to flavor. When all are browned, add 1/2 cup water and cover.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding water if necessary.
(I do the simmering in crock-pot.)

title: brownies
directions: Melt, then cool, chocolate and butter.
Beat until light the eggs and salt.
Add the sugar gradually.
Continue to beat until these ingredients are light and creamy.
Fold in the melted mixture and vanilla.
Add flour; fold in nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in the batter.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
When it is cold, cut into squares.

title: seven minute cake icing
directions: Cook in double boiler.
Have water in bottom of boiler boiling before you put top on.
Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in double boiler with mixer at high speed.
Continue to mix at high speed the entire cooking time.
Stop cooking when icing stands in a peak.
Then add vanilla.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mix. Spread on greased and floured 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together.
Cool; unroll.

title: cabbage roll with sour cream sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion in 2 tablespoons fat in large skillet over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in celery, rice, egg and mustard.
Cook cabbage leaves for 3 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Place beef mixture in cabbage leaves, then roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Place close together in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour tomato puree and water over cabbage rolls.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove the rolls, then stir in sour cream into pan and liquid.
Serve over rolls.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Stir in sauerkraut; mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover bowl tightly and chill in refrigerator at least 12 hours before serving.

title: sea island salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
If dry add more mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thaw potatoes. Mix all ingredients and spread into casserole dish.
Dab top with butter.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: quick "pizza" appetizers
directions: Slice each muffin in half.
Spread pizza sauce over each half, layer cheese and pepperoni, sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
Serve warm.
May be made ahead, covered and reheated.

title: tofu pot pie
directions: Toss the cubes of tofu in a mix of 1 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Brown the coated cubes in oil.
When crispy, add the veggies and cook over medium heat until carrots are soft.

title: chicken chasseurs
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
In hot butter or margarine in a large skillet, saute chicken until golden on all sides.
Add scallions, mushrooms, sugar, salt, lemon juice, apple juice or chicken broth (according to taste preference) and tomatoes.
Cook slowly, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Sprinkle with parsley and chives.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, sour cream, oil and eggs together.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture in pan and sprinkle 1/2 brown sugar and cinnamon mixture over this.
Pour other half of cake mixture in pan and sprinkle the rest of the cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake in 275° oven for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish, place the toast and toss the raisins over the toast.
To the eggs, add 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Pour this mixture into the dish and let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with the 4 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon combination.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: holiday salad(easy and simple)
directions: Mix together cranberries and sugar and refrigerate overnight. Next day, add pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: pina pepper spread(appetizer)
directions: Combine pineapple and taco sauce in small bowl.
Place cream cheese on serving plate in block or cut into individual servings. Spoon pineapple mixture over top.
Serve with taco chips or crackers.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir
together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3 quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Boil
5 minutes
over
medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Stir
constantly
to prevent sticking.
Remove from
heat. Gradually
stir
in chocolate chips until melted. Add
remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch
pan.
Cool at
room
temperature.
Cut
into squares. Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: mothers slaw dressing
directions: Cook together over low heat until thickened. Use over slaw or lettuce.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with a vegetable peeler or knife, if desired.
Cut asparagus pieces and broccoli flowerets in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add carrot and chopped peppers to onion mixture; saute until crisp-tender. Remove from heat; drain.

title: eton mess
directions: Reserve 5 whole strawberries for decorations.
Sprinkle the remaining
strawberries
with sugar and chill for an hour. Fold in cream
and
yogurt.
Add the crushed meringues.
Toss and place in glass bowl.
Top with strawberries.
(If you are unable to find
the meringues in the store, a recipe for them is in this book.) Yields 6 servings.

title: hot crab rolls
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Roll slices lightly with rolling pin.
Drain crab; crumble and mix with cream cheese (I use a fourth more cheese than this).
Spread on bread slices; roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Refrigerate (may freeze for later) cut rolls into thirds.
Roll in melted butter and then in Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: tropical dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Spread pie filling.
Spread undrained pineapple.
Dump dry cake mix around and pour butter around.
Spread coconut and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: barbecued hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, in 10 x 6 x 2-inch nonmetal baking dish.
Micro-cook, covered, for 15 minutes, giving dish a quarter turn every 3 minutes.
Transfer chicken to barbecue grill and grill over hot coals for 5 minutes.
Combine the apricot preserves, Russian dressing and dry onion soup mix.
Brush mixture over chicken.
Grill chicken about 10 minutes more or until done, brushing occasionally with preserve mixture and turning chicken until evenly browned.
Transfer to serving platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: troys pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cherry cups
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half and add nuts and chocolate. Press in muffin cups.
Place cherry in center and top with white dough and another cherry half.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting or leave plain.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs in a mixing bowl.
Add pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, salt, cloves, nutmeg and ginger; beat just until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 40 to 45 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield: 2 pies (6 to 8 servings each).

title: baked lithuanian cheese slices(keptas suris)
directions: Slice cheese into about 1/4-inch thick pieces.
First, dip each piece of cheese in beaten egg (with milk), then in bread crumbs. Place pieces with dabs of butter on them in a buttered glass baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve immediately from same baking dish.
Delicious on dark, Lithuanian rye bread.

title: spam casserole
directions: *Kraft Shells and Cheese is recommended.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and mustard; add milk.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Butter baking dish.
Put cooked macaroni in dish.
Pour sauce over macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Dash with paprika.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until browned and bubbly.

title: chicken casserole(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix soup and water together and put in bottom of large baking dish.
Pour rice over soup mixture.
Place chicken parts over all. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Thaw the broccoli and put into a casserole dish.
Over medium heat, melt butter and saute onions.
Add water (stir constantly). Add flour (stir).
Add cheese and stir until it melts.
Remove pan from burner and stir in beaten eggs.
Pour mixture on top of broccoli and mix.
Pour bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bread crumbs are browned.

title: silver spoon wings
directions: Combine sugar, water, soy sauce, pineapple juice, oil, ginger and garlic powder.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over wings in bowl small enough to cover wings.
Refrigerate and marinate at least 1 full day, stirring occasionally.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, carrots, green peppers and onions in butter until tender, not brown. Stir in flour. Slowly stir in broth and pepper. Stir until thickened. Cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Add cheese and stir until melted. Add pimento. Just before serving, add beer and heat. Season with salt. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy bean tostadas
directions: Arrange tortillas in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes on each side until crisp.
Let cool on a wire rack.

title: golden mushroom burgers
directions: Brown patties and drain grease from pan.
Pour in soup, mushrooms and 1 can water.	Simmer 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk last.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonful into hot buttered skillet.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts; put in bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake mix by directions on box.
Pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
In a saucepan heat margarine and cream cheese until mixture is warm enough to stir in powdered sugar. When smooth, spoon over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.
Do not cut until cold.

title: beaumont inn  corn pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix milk and eggs.
Mix together both mixtures well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake slowly 30 minutes in 350° oven or until done.
Stir from bottom 3 times while baking.
The stirring is what produces the custard consistency.

title: graham cracker loaf
directions: Roll crackers.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Add cream, if too dry.
Form into a roll, roll in wax paper and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cut in slices and serve with whipped cream and maraschino cherry on top.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in larger	mixer
bowl at high speed.
Add eggs one at a time,
beating well after each addition.
Gradually add sugar; continue
creaming
at
high speed until light and fluffy. By hand,
stir
frosting
mix,
flour and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for
to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours before removing from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and bring to boil over low heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and chop.
Saute onion in margarine. Cook rice and drain.
Add remaining ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbling. Do not cover.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In medium saucepan, over high heat, heat vinegar, sugar, spice, salt and bay leaves to boiling.
Place shelled eggs in 2-quart jar.
Add vinegar mixture to the eggs; let stand 2 days, then use.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies by hand with potato masher.
Set aside as this is your crumb mixture.
(This will look like dirt when mashed.)
Mix together cream cheese, 10x sugar and butter.
Set aside.

title: pecan braisers
directions: Beat egg white until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar and vanilla gradually with mixer.
Feed in pecans.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 30 minutes, then let set in oven for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven.

title: banana blueberry delight
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch
pan and brown at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all these together.
Chill for several hours (the longer the better).

title: meringue kisses - cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add confectioners sugar, vinegar, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by 1 teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brunch turnovers
directions: Let frozen pastry stand at room temperature about 1 hour or until thawed. In a small saucepan, cook onion in hot margarine or butter until tender but not brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Pour Ranch mix into container of sour cream and stir well. Make sure that all the dry mix has been stirred into the sour cream.
Cut vegetables of your choice and dip.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and milk. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Dough will be stiff.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out on floured counter 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutters and decorate or sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° on an ungreased sheet for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry-pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan (in oven) while preheating oven.
Add sugar and pineapple (include juice).
Mix well.
Rinse cranberries in colander and pick out mushy ones.
Remove any stems.
Sprinkle cranberries over pineapple mixture (evenly).
Pour prepared cake mix over pineapple/cranberry mix.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pat out like biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: 7-up dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Freeze.
Serve as fruit cups.
Place in muffin cups.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix eggplant with other ingredients.
Cover with buttered crumbs and bake at 300° until brown.

title: one-cup cobbler
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and flour. Slowly add milk; mix well with electric mixer. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour batter over butter, then cover with fruit. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour
and
salt
together;
add
shortening.
Mix well with pastry
fork.	Beat egg lightly in separate container; add water and
vinegar.
Add
to first mixture.
Roll into balls and store in
freezer
until
ready to use.
If not used immediately, will keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days.

title: chicken breasts with orange sauce
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Sprinkle inside of chicken breasts with 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine 2 tablespoons softened margarine, parsley, onion and tarragon; mix well.
Spread about 1 teaspoon margarine mixture over inside of each chicken breast. Fold long sides of chicken over margarine and secure with 1/2 teaspoon salt and paprika.
Saute chicken in 2 tablespoons melted margarine over medium heat in a large skillet until golden brown on both sides, turning once.

title: all in one salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shoestring potatoes, together and refrigerate at least one hour.
Add the shoestring potatoes just before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
In a large bowl, add chicken soup, sour cream and 1/2 of the enchilada sauce.
Mix together.
In a large baking dish, open taco shell and fill with a small amount of mixture. Roll up and place filled shells side by side.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce on top and bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Top with shredded cheese and serve.

title: butter rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour and Crisco together in large bowl until it resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and mix well to make dough.
Roll dough out relatively thin.
Cut into 6 squares.
In the center of each square, add 1 pat of butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold over; place in deep skillet and bake until golden brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: Put a tablespoon of meat into a tortilla shell, dipped into sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll.
Place into pan.
Fill up. Add remaining sauce, meat, chili and cheese.
Top with cheese. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: spinach and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust and line 9-inch pie plate.
With wire whisk, beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and onions. Stir in spinach (thawed and well drained) and cheese.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°; turn oven control to 325° and bake for 35 minutes.
Quiche is cooked when inserted knife in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: salsa-topped chicken breasts
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Combine chili powder and next 3 ingredients; sprinkle over chicken.
Melt butter in a nonstick skillet.
Add chicken and cook 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until done.
Stir cilantro into black bean mixture.
Serve over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: champagne punch
directions: Place the lemon juice in a large punch bowl.
Add enough sugar to sweeten.
Add soda water and plenty of ice cubes and stir well. Then add maraschino, curacao and brandy.
Stir well.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour and margarine.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake until light brown.
Cool.

title: espresso stuffed cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage and boil in hot water until tender.
Cook rice (it will make about 2 cups).
Add remaining ingredients all together, along with the cabbage and rice.
Stir and put in pan in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves lots.

title: pecan and graham cracker pralines
directions: Place graham crackers (broken in fourths) in a large pan.
Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Let cool. Store in airtight container.

title: memaw's jelly
directions: Mix berries and Sure-Jell and bring to a boil. Add sugar and bring to a hard boil. Boil for 1 minute. Process.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together milk, molasses or honey, oil and egg.
Add fruit so that raisins and dates are moistened and plumped up.

title: upside-down blueberry pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pancake mix according to package directions. Set aside.
In a 10-inch pie plate (in oven), melt butter and remove from heat.
Spoon berries in bottom of pie plate. Carefully pour batter atop. Bake 18 minutes or until top springs back when tapped.
Loosen edges and invert onto serving plate.
Cut in wedges and serve with maple flavor syrup. Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine melted margarine with stuffing; put in 8 x 10-inch baking dish, reserving 1 cup for topping.
Mix together zucchini, carrots, onion, chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over stuffing. Top with reserved stuffing and grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: planters punch
directions: Mix ingredients and shake.
Pour into chilled glass filled with ice.

title: peach honey
directions: Process peaches in food processor or blender until smooth. Combine peaches and honey in saucepan.
Mix cornstarch, lemon juice and water.
Add to peaches; heat until thick and bubbly. Stir in extract.
Use over ice cream, pancakes or waffles.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese (at room temperature) with milk and onion. Add diced chicken and butter.
Push perforated holes together in crescent rolls to make a square.
Place 1/3 cup of chicken mixture on center of square and bring up ends and pinch together on top. Brush tops with extra melted butter and sprinkle seasoned bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
I always double the ingredients to make enough for 4 to 6 people.

title: clark's blue plate special
directions: Turn oven to 400°.
Put potato rounds or Tater Tots on bottom of 11 x 7-inch glass or aluminum pan.
Cook for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cook turkey (or beef) in a skillet on range top. Remove potatoes from oven and add meat over the top of potatoes. Put broccoli as next layer.
Mix celery soup and milk and pour over broccoli.
Cover with grated cheese.
Garnish with Durkee onions.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter gradually.
Add sugar and vanilla. Beat!
Beat!
Beat!
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 3 minutes after adding each egg.
(Repeat second egg; beat 3 minutes, third egg, beat 3 minutes.)
Place in baked pie shell and refrigerate. Top with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a large saucepan, bring pineapple and syrup to a boil. Remove from the heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in buttermilk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill.

title: italian cake
directions: In large bowl cream margarine, shortening: add sugar and beat well:
add egg yolks, vanilla, and beat.
Add coconut.
In separate bowl sift flour and soda together twice before adding to first mixture.
Add buttermilk and flour alternating in 3 additions.
Start with dry and end with dry until all has been creamed together.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Prepare 3 well greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 - 30 minutes, until cake springs back when pressed by hand.
