Cool completely before icing.

title: great banana pudding
directions: Combine instant pudding with cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and crumbled vanilla wafers sprinkled on top.
Chill. Tastes great!
Ron Wood loves it.

title: black bean salsa
directions: In a bowl, stir together relish, beans, radishes, lime juice and cumin. Let stand, covered for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lasagna sandwiches
directions: Combine the first four ingredients; spread on four slices of bread.
Top each with four bacon pieces, two tomato slices and a slice of cheese.
Top with remaining bread.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour over ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: pat's punch
directions: Place strawberries and orange juice into blender and blend until mushy.
Pour into punch bowl and add crushed pineapple (syrup also).
Add Canada Dry ginger ale.

title: jazzy beef balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; let stand 10 minutes.
Combine ground beef and bread crumbs.
Stir in ketchup mixture.
Cut Cheddar cheese into small cubes (about 1/4 inch cubes).
Shape meat around cubes.
You can spear and cook in fondue pot for 1 1/2 minutes or slowly cook in a frying pan.

title: boterkoek(dutch butter cake)
directions: Mix in order given.
If using butter instead of margarine you may need a bit more flour (up to one-half cup).
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.
You can make a design by pressing down on top with a fork.
Brush top with beaten egg white.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes, or until golden in color.

title: ever green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
May use different flavor Kool-Aid for other colors.
Also different kinds of fruit juice, to suit the occasion and color theme.
Serves 50 people.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and add cocoa, sugar, vanilla, milk, butter and salt.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(When you test the pie, if there is still a lot of wiggling, pie may need to cook another 5 minutes or so.)
Chill at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: nellie bealmer's broccoli casserole
directions: Combine together all ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Add to rice and cheese mixture.
Place in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in a large pan. Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Debone and cut up. Return chicken to mixture. Bring to a boil again. Add noodles and cook until tender.

title: icing sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add the dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Roll small amount of dough into a ball.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix pudding and buttermilk and add Cool Whip to mixture.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Chill overnight.

title: tuna burger
directions: Mix together ingredients and form into patties.
Spray pan with Pam or use 2 teaspoons canola or safflower oil and brown patties.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Scrub beets, leaving small amount of green top on. Cook beets until soft. Rub off skin and green top. Cut beets in chunks or if small, put in jars. Then boil the vinegar, beet juice (you get from pot you cooked beets in), sugar and salt. Pour over beets in jar. Add 3 to 4 cloves per jar. Makes about 5 quarts. Can in hot water bath 10 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar with margarine.
Add eggs. Begin adding dry ingredients and alternate with milk until completely mixed.
Add floured blueberries.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no sugar fruit bars
directions: Combine dates, raisins, prunes and water; boil together 5 minutes, then add stick of oleo and set aside to cool.
Add sifted dry ingredients and eggs (beaten) to fruit mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 25 minutes at 350° heat.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 1/3 cup mixture in 8 ounces hot water.

title: chicken supreme(skillet)
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Slice diagonally in 1/2-inch pieces.
In a skillet, brown chicken in shortening until golden. Pour off fat, add soup and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes and zucchini. Cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread with 3/4 cup grated cheese and 2 cups crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes a large casserole dish; can be divided.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Roll chops in flour and brown well on both sides in a little salad oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Top with potato slices and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons cheese.
Spread onion slices on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water and pour over all.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Serves 2.

title: crab dip
directions: Thaw crab, if frozen.
Drain and reserve liquid.

Slice crab. Reserve a few pieces for garnish. Blend together the cream cheese with all the remaining ingredients and the reserved crab liquid. Stir in crab. Spoon in dish. Bake at 325° about 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Garnish with reserved pieces of crab and additional green onions.
Serve with French bread.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Stir yeast into water. Set aside. Stir sugar and margarine together. Add egg to margarine mixture. Stir in yeast water mixture. Add flour. Stir in airtight bowl and keep refrigerated. Keeps for several days. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned in 1/2 filled muffin tins.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Fry chicken until brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and put in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover with foil and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in cooking oil; add green chilies, cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup, enchilada sauce, salt and pepper.
Layer tortillas and meat sauce in greased baking pan. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: out of this world fruit salad
directions: Note:
Use any fresh, canned or frozen fruit.

title: miss julia's glazed apples
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water on to boil.
Add cinnamon and coloring.
When syrup starts to boil, add apples.
Cook until apples shine or the syrup is almost jelly.

title: quickie sweet pickle
directions: Slice thinly; layer in wide mouth container.
Add sugar, 1 to 2 cups per layer.
Continue to layer pickle and sugar.
Cover and refrigerate 48 hours.
If not sweet enough, add sugar as desired.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Combine all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: nutty blond brownies
directions: Cream butter, all sugar, egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Pour into a well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wiltproof salad
directions: Thinly slice mushrooms.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, onion, salt, sugar, pepper and mustard.
Add to mushrooms to coat.
Cut cauliflower into flowerets and thinly slice.
Add to mushrooms along with celery and green pepper.
Let marinate at least one hour.
Just before serving, stir in tomatoes.
Improves with marinating.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill until firm.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Top each with pecan half.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Roll warm cookies in very fine granulated sugar.
Yields 6 dozen.
Store in airtight container.
Will not ship well.

title: banana chip chewies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mash up bananas and fold in. Fold in chocolate chips.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tasty meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in cream; then mix with egg, beef, sausage and seasonings.
Shape into cocktail balls.
Brown on all sides in hot shortening.
Pour off excess fat and drain on paper towels.

title: keftetas (greek meatballs)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except flour and oil.
Roll the mixture into small balls.
Then roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: easy minestone soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic in heavy pan until meat is browned.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans, corn and remaining ingredients except pasta.
Cook and stir about 30 minutes.
Add pasta and cook until it's tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of butter in a skillet on stove.
In a roaster or Dutch oven put 1 cup raw white rice. Season with minced onion and parsley flakes.
Place pork chops on rice, then pour beef consomme and 1 can water over pork chops and rice.
Cover the pan and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in bottom of pan you are using.
Add peaches (drained).
Sprinkle with sugar.
Sift together flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Then add milk to mixture. Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mahatma golden rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add margarine to rice and stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix dressing with margarine; spread 1/2 in greased casserole dish. Place onions and celery on mix. Place all chicken pieces on mix; add rest of dressing mix. Mix chicken broth and soups; pour over dressing. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Peel and cut up tomatoes.
Place in a large pot.
Add chopped jalapenos, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Add seasonings and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil gently until thick (4 to 6 hours).
Pour immediately into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: brown stone front chocolate cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Mix butter or margarine with sugar.
Beat in egg yolks; mix well.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in 4 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: Spray heavy skillet with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Cook chicken or turkey over medium-high heat until browned, turning frequently.
Add choice of sliced vegetables.
When vegetables begin to get tender, add salad dressing and thin with cooking wine.
I like fat-free Honey Dijon with white cooking wine.
Heat through and simmer.
Serve with rice.
Makes dinner in 1/2 to 3/4 hour, start to finish.
Serves at least 4 with leftovers.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form a ball.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soups, milk, broth and green chilies.
In a lightly greased casserole dish, layer tortillas and chicken.
Pour soup mixture over the top, then top with grated cheese, if desired. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Grease and flour a round pie pan.
Combine ingredients and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat milk, onion, butter, salt, celery salt and pepper to scalding in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Sprinkle each serving with paprika and snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: green beans mandarin
directions: Pour liquid from beans; save it.
Lightly brown almonds in oil; add celery and saute 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup bean liquid, stock base, soy sauce, sugar and vinegar.
Cover; simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in beans and heat until hot.
Add cornstarch mixed with water; heat just until sauce thickens.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine jelly, chili sauce and broth in large pan, plus 1 bottle of water.
Mix ground beef, eggs and bread crumbs, plus salt and pepper to taste.
Form small meat balls and drop into boiling juice.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours until sauce thickens.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Divide and chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll and cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes. Always double or triple this recipe because it only makes 2 dozen.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saute onion in butter; add ham, corned beef and garlic.
Heat well.
Mix in flour; add beaten egg, stirring quickly, so that the egg does not set.
Add sauerkraut, spices, parsley and beef stock. Cook and stir until mixture forms a paste.
Spread onto a platter in a thin layer and chill well (4 hours).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in flour; dip in beaten eggs and roll in white bread crumbs.
(Use 5 to 6 slices bread, crumbled in the blender.)
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown.
May be frozen and reheated at 350°.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use approximately 3 teaspoons per cup.
Keep in airtight container.

title: crunchy popcorn mix
directions: In a large bowl, toss the popped corn with the cereal, soybean nuts and raisins.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: Cook beans in water (add 2 tablespoons oil, 2 cloves and 1 bay leaf to water).
Saute chopped celery and minced garlic.
Add tomato, 1 teaspoon puree, pepper, 1/2 cup water and salt.
Boil slowly, then pour over beans (which should be well done).
Cook 15 minutes.
Remove and mash small amount of beans and then return to pot.
Add uncooked pasta.
Add oregano.
Bring to boil, adding more water, if necessary.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix and cook over low heat until thick.
Save egg whites for meringue.

title: blackberry syrup
directions: Boil berries and water.
Strain and press through strainer. Add sugar to juice.
Discard berries.
Boil juice mixture 5 to 8 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
One half cup serving contains 81 calories.

title: gingerbread pancakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Combine milk and next 3 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter onto hot nonstick griddle.

title: mandelgeback(german)
directions: *Roast almonds with 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan until slightly browned, stirring constantly.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together tomatoes, soups, cheese, onion and chili powder. Layer chicken, chips and soup mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Top with chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Shape into small balls. Roll in sesame seed.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
They are ready to eat and enjoy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: *Or your choice of cold cuts.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook chicken in water 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and dice into large bowl.
Add cubed bread, diced potatoes and carrots.
Saute chopped celery and chopped onion in 2 tablespoons oleo until clear.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add celery-onion mixture to chicken and bread. Add egg-milk mixture.
Add seasonings.
Stir.
Moisten with chicken broth.
Place in casserole and bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: new potato salad
directions: In a large bowl stir mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and sugar together until well blended.
Add prepared potatoes and onions. Toss to mix well.
Cover and chill 4 hours.
If desired, sprinkle top with chopped parsley.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix and let set.

title: oatmeal raisin pancakes
directions: Mix together and fry.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve 1 large package jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and juice, cranberry sauce, orange juice, sugar and nuts.
Blend well. Put dish in refrigerator until firm.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Use a container that will be airtight when covered.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over vegetables.
Sprinkle sugar over bacon.
Spread mayonnaise to cover top.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: In crockpot or saucepan large enough to accommodate the meatballs, pour in one bottle of barbecue sauce, any flavour. Fill the bottle with red wine and add to the sauce.
Mix the two together and add meatballs.
Simmer on low heat 1/2 - 1 hour.
Let stand several hours to absorb the flavour.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
While it is browning, cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain grease off meat.
Stir in onion, celery, pepper, mushrooms, soups and tomato sauce.
Salt to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce and olives.
Mix together well and carefully stir in noodles.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and top with grated cheese for the last 5 minutes baking time.

title: liverwurst schnitzel
directions: Coat liverwurst with flour; dip in egg and coat with crumbs.

title: creole okra
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in hot fat until onion is golden, stirring frequently.
Add okra.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caramel float
directions: In a heavy skillet over medium heat, carmelize (melt) 1/3 cup sugar until it becomes an amber colored liquid.
Gradually pour in boiling water and stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill in a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Gradually add milk, beating at low speed.
Add light cream, salt and caramelized sugar.
Beat at low speed until all ingredients are combined.
Pour into serving glasses and top each with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Peel shrimp, uncooked and deveined.
Make a roux (dark) of flour and oil.
Add shrimp to this for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
Smother okra and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes when okra is nearly cooked.
Then add water, bay leaf, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and roux to this.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: rick's cheesy potatoes
directions: Take small red potatoes (new potatoes) and half them.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Take green onions and saute them in butter until tender.
Take Velveeta cheese and melt it into the butter and green onions.
Take the potatoes and drain them and pour the cheese mixture on top of them and serve warm.
Delicious!!!

title: 4 week bran muffins
directions: Break eggs into a very large bowl or pot.
Beat with rotary beater until well blended; beat in shortening, buttermilk and sugar thoroughly.
Add soda and salt; stir well.
Mix in Raisin Bran.
Add flour and stir just until mixed.
It makes a thick batter.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
It will keep for 4 weeks in a 40° refrigerator.

title: opa stehling's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients into large saucepan and simmer until everything disintegrates.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit (keep juice); mix together and chill.

title: penney's war pie
directions: Brown meat and onion (drain).
Add seasonings and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with corn bread batter.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until the corn bread is golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Press with a fork on cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Roll in ball; roll ball in ground nuts and parsley.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and beaten eggs in large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with soured milk.
Add baking soda to dough, mixing until combined.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cooking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: company broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli as instructed on package.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and drain.
Arrange in greased pan with sliced water chestnuts. Mix soup and milk; pour over broccoli.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with onions; bake 5 more minutes.

title: crunchy fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Salt and pepper fillets.
Combine sour cream, mayo and dressing mix.
Totally coat both sides of fish. Roll fillets in the crushed French fried onions.

title: lemon delight
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to the boiling point.
Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and salt, add them to the water and cook until mixture is thick and clear, set aside.
Beat the egg yolks and add the lemon juice and grated lemon rind; mix well. Add the egg mixture to the cornstarch mixture.
Break the Angel Food cake into chunks and add them to the lemon mixture.
Fold together until well mixed.
Pour into a buttered Angel Food cake pan; cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pork chop & potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly oiled skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt to taste; set aside.

title: shrimply scrumptious(shrimp creole)
directions: Saute celery, onions and pepper in oil until tender; stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until shrimp is tender; stir occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.
This recipe makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla together.
Add egg mixture to apple mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: poor valley waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg yolks, buttermilk and melted butter.
Fold in egg whites last.
Bake on hot well-greased griddle.

title: nalesniki(cheese crepes)
directions: Lightly oil skillet.
Heat to medium high.
Pour batter into oval shapes (usually 2 per skillet).
Edges will curl.
Cook until light brown, then turn.
Roll up with cottage cheese; sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 12 to 15 crepes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch buttered pie plate 2/3 full with sliced apples. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
In a saucepan, melt 3/4 cup margarine.
Add ingredients and mix well. Pour hot over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: big soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl, beat butter on low speed for 30 seconds to soften.
Gradually add the sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture. Shape in 1 1/2-inch balls (1 heaping tablespoon dough each).
Roll in the colored sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 1/2-inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until light brown and still puffed (do not overbake).
Let stand 2 minutes before transferring to cool.
Makes 24 (3-inch) cookies.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll into little balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in pie crust. Chill 3 to 4 hours until firm.
Top with your favorite filling.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Beat the eggs.
Mix sour cream, vanilla, Kahlua and oil into egg mixture. Add chocolate pudding and cake mix.
Beat with mixer until blended. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: polynesian beef bites
directions: Combine ground beef, oatmeal, water chestnuts, monosodium glutamate, onion salt, garlic salt, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, Tabasco sauce and milk.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls using about 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Put under broiler until brown on all sides.
Shake pan frequently to keep balls round.
Drain off grease.
Set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix together sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add pineapple juice, bouillon, vinegar and 2 teaspoons soy sauce.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly until thickened and clear.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in pineapple and chopped green pepper.
Combine sauce and meatballs.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Provide wooden picks for spearing.
Serve sauce and meatballs in a chafing dish.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
This makes a muffin-like batter.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Lightly fold ingredients together and put in crock-pot. Cover and cook on high for about 3 hours.

title: molded tapioca cream
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and continue beating until mixture will form soft peaks.
Mix tapioca, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk, egg yolks and gelatin in a saucepan. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: broiled coconut frosting
directions: Cream butter; add 1 cup brown sugar.
Add 2 tablespoons light cream; mix	well.
Stir in coconut.
Spread mixture over warm cake.
Broil
4 to 8-inches from heat, about 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve cake warm.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Add ground meat.
Mix cornstarch and seasoning into pizza sauce.
Add sauce to meat and stir well. When mix thickens, add cheese by thirds.
Stir well.
Serve with Italian bread cut into bite size pieces.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onions in the bacon grease.
Mix in all ingredients, except the shrimp.
Leave bacon in mixture.
Do not add water.
Simmer mixture for 45 minutes, then add shrimp.
Finish cooking for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Next layer on the baked potatoes, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs with water and pour over the top.
Add sausage.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for approximately 25 minutes.
May substitute ham or bacon for sausage.
You may also like to add green pepper or onion.
This is good for a crowd.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Then alternate with flour (to which you have added the baking powder) and milk.
Begin and end with flour.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hot chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered pie pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Serve hot with ice cream.

title: mixed fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep refrigerated.

title: chip dip
directions: Blend together and chill.
The longer chilled, the better. Good also with carrot or celery sticks.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Put mashed potatoes in a casserole bowl and add all ingredients except the cheese. Crumble the bacon before it is added. Mix these and pour cheese on top. Bake on 350 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: crispy fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, paprika and salt in bowl.
Place crackers and potato chip crumbs on waxed paper.
Dip fillets in margarine, then in crumbs, coating well.
Place in shallow baking pan in single layer.
Bake 10 minutes, then broil 5-inches from broiler for 6 to 8 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve with lemon slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In butter, in large saucepan, over medium heat, saute onion until tender (4 minutes).
Meanwhile, trim broccoli stalks and cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut remaining broccoli into flowerets.
Add water to saucepan; bring to boiling.
Add broccoli and reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 7 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients; simmer 20 minutes or until broccoli is very tender.
(If using thawed broccoli, omit 7 minute cooking.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until it falls apart.
Cool.
Save stock.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Cover chicken with olive oil and sugar. Cook tomatoes, onion, celery and seasonings slowly for 1 hour. Cook spaghetti in chicken stock until done.
Add all ingredients except cheese and simmer for 1 hour.
Put into two large casseroles and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese bubbles at 300° to 350°.
Serves 12.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for one hour.

title: lastrada
directions: Cube bread and cover bottom of slightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese and meat over bread.
Mix beaten eggs and milk. Pour over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend all
ingredients	together with a mixer.	Pour in container.	Refrigerate.
This
is an excellent salad dressing and makes nice gifts.
(Can use small jelly jars.)

title: bourbon balls
directions: Soak pecans in bourbon for 24 hours.
Cream powdered sugar with margarine.
Add pecans; chill.
Shape into one inch balls and place on cookie sheet in freezer until hard.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put 2 qts. water in a lg. pot and next 4 ingredients, cook for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, oil, butter, salt and pepper and simmer for about 40 minutes.
Mix a little water with cornmeal mix and add to soup.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Very good served with cornbread.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes, then drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: parmesan cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts. Top with a maraschino cherry.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a greased baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli or cauliflower as directed on package; drain. Place in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over vegetable.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle on crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Boil 1 box macaroni in salt water until tender.
Drain. Butter a baking dish.
Alternate layers of macaroni and oysters, sprinkled with cheese.
Thicken the liquid from oysters with cracker crumbs.
Spread over the top.
Dot with butter and cheese. Bake one-half hour at 350°.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix
cocoa,
flour, salt and sugar.
Slowly stir in the boiling
water
and
return
to the heat.
Bring to a boil and cook
gently until thickened, stirring constantly.	Remove pan from
heat.
Stir
2 or 3 tablespoons of the chocolate mixture into
the lightly beaten egg yolks.
Return to the heat.
Stir in cornstarch which has been dissolved in 2 tablespoons water. Cook gently
2 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat
and stir
in
butter and flavorings.
Cool slightly and pour
into baked
crust.
Cover with meringue, sealing to the crust
on edges.
Bake at 350° until golden.	Time of preparation: 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and wax.
Put in refrigerator to firm up for a few minutes.

title: savory country-style ribs
directions: Place ribs in large pot; cover with water.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour or until ribs are tender.
Drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In medium saucepan saute onions in butter until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until ribs are nicely glazed, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pineapple sparkle
directions: Will also need straws and frosted glasses.

title: texas eggs
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Melt butter in skillet and scramble eggs in it.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cooked bacon, onion, green peppers and mushrooms.
Warm soup and sherry together. Spread over all.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake 50 minutes at 250°.

title: chicken barley soup
directions: Cook chicken in 2 quarts water.
Remove chicken; cool and cut up.
Add remaining ingredients and cook about 1/2 to 1 hour. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Mix beans, ketchup and sauce. Add ground beef and onion.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: butter icing
directions: * Add more to get proper spreading consistency.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil.
Add garlic and ginger; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add sherry, soy sauce, honey, orange peel, sesame seed and Tabasco sauce.
Place chops in large shallow dish or plastic bag; add marinade.
Cover; refrigerate for 1 hour. Turn chops occasionally.
Remove chops from marinade; pour marinade into small saucepan.
Place chops on grill about 5 inches from source of heat.
Grill 10 minutes on each side.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine cornstarch and water; stir.

title: carolyna's potato dumplings
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Mash thoroughly and set aside to cool.
Cube toasted bread; toss in melted butter until all sides are coated and browned.
When potatoes are cool, whip until fluffy.
Add egg, salt and white pepper.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Cut up desired amount of raw chicken into bite size pieces. Put chicken and all other ingredients into a crock-pot.
Cook all day on low in crock-pot.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until blended.
Put in refrigerator.
When ready to eat, place by spoonful in well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator, covered.

title: batter for shrimp or onion rings
directions: Mix together flour, oil and milk.
Beat well.
Add egg and beat again.
Roll shrimp in dry flour, then in batter, fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; brown on both sides in hot oil.
Remove chops and add soup mix, mushroom soup and water to pan drippings.
Bring to a boil.
Put green pepper and rice in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with chops.
Pour mixture over chops and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar and eggs one at a time.
Mix half of the flour, half the milk, salt and baking powder.
Add remainder of milk and flour and then the oil and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan.
Put in cool oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: veg-all soup
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Mix other ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Add salt and seasoning to water and vinegar.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add frozen fish.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and serve with melted butter.

title: lamb chops
directions: Melt butter; add vinegar and sprinkle of garlic powder.
Pour over lamb chops.
Sear under broiler only until brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and seasoning salt on both sides.
If necessary, transfer to a baking pan.
Add enough water in bottom of pan to avoid sticking.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours. Serve with mint jelly.

title: fajitas(texas style)
directions: Prepare meat as directed, then layer ingredients as desired on flour tortilla.
Roll with one end folded inward.
Serves 4.

title: quiche
directions: Thaw 2 pie shells and put cheese in bottom, then bacon.
Beat eggs, cream, salt and pepper and pour on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake on cookie sheet 40 minutes at 375° or until set. Let stand 10 minutes or cover and heat later.
Freezes nicely.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in salad oil until tender.
Add ground beef, stirring occasionally, until meat loses red color. Add salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Stir in paste, water and catsup.
Cover and simmer about three hours.
When sauce is ready, cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Arrange on platter and pour hot sauce over it.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil together 7 cups water and sugar and allow to cool.
Brew tea bags in 4 cups water until black.
Mix 2 mixtures with lemonade and orange juice.
Then add brandy and freeze.
To serve:
Fill glass 1/2 to 2/3 full with slush and top off with 7-Up.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in 2 cups hot water.
Let water cool; add yeast, dissolve and add slightly beaten eggs, oil and 3 cups flour.
Using a wooden spoon, beat in 2 cups flour, 1 cup at a time, then add remaining flour and knead until smooth.
Oil bowl and turn dough once in bowl.
Cover and leave in a warm place for about 2 hours or until double in size.
Divide dough into 3 parts. Roll out on a floured surface.
Spread each part with 1/4 cup butter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Roll and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make dressing of eggs, sugar, vinegar and oleo.
Cook until thickened.
While hot, add Philadelphia cheese.
Put in refrigerator.
Mix fruit cocktail, pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Beat package of Dream Whip and mix with cold dressing.
Stir in fruit and refrigerate.
May be made a day ahead.

title: strawberry peach pie(plan ahead.  needs to chill.)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Spread over the bottom and up the sides of the crust. Cut peach slices in half, if desired.
Arrange over cream cheese. Combine the strawberries and glaze.
Spoon over peaches. Refrigerate for up to 4 hours before serving.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and cook over low heat approximately 1 minute, stirring well to dissolve sugar.
Add butter, heating to melt.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to harden.

title: squash casserole #2
directions: Melt butter and combine with half the stuffing.
Pat into bottom of a 2-quart oblong glass dish.
Cook squash and onions together until tender.
Drain. Combine with other ingredients and pour over stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, 3/4 cup
brown
sugar,
oil, salt and nutmeg well. Take out 1/4 cup
of
mixture.
Add
to that 1 teaspoon brown sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Set aside for topping.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 370° for 50 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine all ingredients and sprinkle dry jello over top.
Mix completely.
Serve chilled.

title: confetti caramel corn
directions: Heat the oven to 300°. Place cereal in a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Saute beef with onion and garlic until brown; drain fat. Puree tomatoes with juice in blender. Add with water and bouillon cubes to pan. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Add orzo and vegetables and simmer 15 minutes.

title: south sea salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package; drain. In large bowl, combine rotini, tuna, oranges, celery and apple. In small bowl, blend cottage cheese, mayonnaise, salt and lemon juice. Add to rotini mixture; toss to coat. Cover; chill thoroughly. Before serving, stir gently; top with paprika.

title: herb lemon chicken breasts
directions: Combine lemon pepper seasoning blend with flour on a large plate, pat chicken dry, and roll in flour mixture. Heat butter in large skillet, add chicken and brown on both sides, about 3 minutes each side. Meanwhile, remove zest from lemon, squeeze juice from lemon, and mix zest and juice with chicken stock. Pour over chicken, cover and cook for 15 minutes. Remove lid and cook for an additional 5 minutes or until juice run clear.

title: spreader burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Lay halves of hamburger buns on broiler pan.
Spread mixture on buns thinly.
Put oven rack in center of oven.
Broil until done.

title: chile verde
directions: Cut pork into 1 1/2-inch chunks and sear in hot oil until brown on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Simmer over medium heat, uncovered, until meat is tender and will shred with a fork, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Spanish rice and a green salad.
Makes 5 servings.

title: peanut butter paisley brownies
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter in large mixer bowl.
Add sugar and brown sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to peanut butter mixture.
Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon syrup over top. Carefully spread with remaining batter.
Swirl with spatula or knife for marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: english muffin canape
directions: Mix all ingredients and put on 12 muffin halves.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
To serve, cut each muffin in 6 pieces. Put on broiler pan.
Broil until bubbly.
Makes 72 pieces.

title: borag
directions: Open phyllo dough and lay flat.
Cut in half.
Pour half the butter in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put half the phyllo dough in the dish; turn the edges under.
Mix three cheeses and eggs. Carefully spread on top of phyllo.
Place other half of phyllo on top; turn edges under.
Pour remaining butter over top.
Make sure edges are sealed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Let sit 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve with fruit and salad for luncheon or as a side dish with beef or ham.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Add onion, pepper, mushrooms and sugar to sauces and simmer until macaroni is ready.
Cook macaroni partially done; drain. Brown ground beef.
Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 40 minutes or so at 350°.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine the eggs, mayonnaise, soup and grated onion; mix well.
Fold in broccoli and grated cheese.
Place mixture in a greased casserole dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: herb crescents
directions: Combine sour cream, chopped onion, parsley, poultry seasoning and ground celery seed.
Unroll cans of crescent dinner rolls; cut and separate into triangles.
Fill, roll and top with paprika, celery seed, etc.
Bake as directed on crescent cans.

title: ava's baked apples
directions: Wash apples.
Cut in halves and then fourths.
Line a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with 1 layer of apples.
Sprinkle some sugar over first layer of apples.
Melt margarine and pour a small amount over sugar.
Layer some more apples, then margarine and rest of sugar.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: blushing peach pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Cut or rub in margarine.
Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture over bottom of pie crust in pan.
Put peaches over mixture.
Sprinkle with water.
Put rest of dry mixture on top, covering peaches.
Bake 40 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble bread in blender, one slice at a time, then mix with oleo.
In a saucepan, drain juice from pineapple and add sugars and flour.
Cook until thick.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: In a 2-quart glass baking dish (microwavable), combine butter, onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic to cook on High in the microwave for 4 to 5 minutes, until soft, but not brown.
Stir. Add Worcestershire sauce, Season-All, Tabasco sauce and crawfish tails.
In a small bowl, combine water and cornstarch; mix well. Add to mixture; mix well and cover.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stop; stir well and return to microwave on High for an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Put all vegetables in a large salad bowl.
Set aside.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Peel and cube the potatoes, then place in a large saucepan. Add water and the salt.
Bring to a boil, then cook until tender. Mash the potatoes in the stock.
Saute the onion in the butter until transparent, then add to the potatoes.
Add the cream and heat thoroughly.

title: italian easter bread
directions: In a large pot, mix dry ingredients together.
Form a well in center and add eggs and oil.
Mix yeast and warm water; let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add yeast to well.
Knead until dough is firm.
Place on cookie sheet covered with a clean, dry towel to rise (approximately 8 hours).
Bless dough and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves according to size.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Wash zucchini and slice thinly.
Set aside.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil; be careful not to burn.
Add zucchini and cover.
Stir occasionally to prevent zucchini from sticking; cook until soft.
Discard water that has collected in pot from zucchini.
Add tomatoes and oregano to taste.
Stir and simmer gently until done.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lola's chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken or use breasts only.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Have ready the soups, mushrooms, pimento and Velveeta cheese.

title: potato chip-tuna casserole
directions: Blend the mushroom soup and milk.
Add minced onion and bring slowly
to	the
boiling
point,
stirring	constantly. Season
to taste
with
salt and pepper.
Arrange half of the crushed potato chips in the bottom of the casserole dish.	Top with
half of the flaked or grated tuna.
Repeat layers.
Pour mushroom
soup mixture
over
all	and garnish top with whole potato
chips. Bake
in
a
moderate
oven, 350° for about 25 minutes, or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.

title: barbecues for 150 people
directions: Cook meats, onion, peppers and celery until well done.
Add other ingredients and cook slow for some time.

title: alleluia sausage
directions: Cut onions and green pepper; put in a frying pan.
Stir in sausages.
Cook on medium heat for 25 minutes.
Add Ragu sauce. Cook another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water, and salt.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add color and jell-o and stir well. Let cool.
Put in strawberries in shell, pour over sauce, chill. Top with whipped cream.

title: russian pancakes(mennonite recipe)
directions: Beat egg; add flour and salt.
Add milk gradually and beat until batter is smooth.
This is a very thin batter.
Pour some pancake batter onto a hot greased frying pan, allowing it to run over the entire surface of the pan in a thin layer.
When edges are golden brown, turn and fry on the other side.
These may be served with butter and sugar and syrup or jam.
They are also good with applesauce, cinnamon and sugar.
Makes about 8 pancakes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, water and cocoa or chocolate. Cook over medium heat, until it slightly thickens.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Serve hot over cake and/or ice cream.

title: jezebel relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric beater.
Serve with crackers or as a relish for beef.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and butter, then add salt and syrup. Add pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until set and pastry is nicely browned at 375°, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Add brown sugar and egg; mix well.
Add vanilla, dry ingredients and nuts.
Spread into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, flour and milk.
Beat egg whites and add to mixture last.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake at 450° in unbaked pie crust.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together. Add the next 3 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Mix drained cherries and sugar.
Pour over batter in dish.
Dot with margarine and pour boiling cherry juice (add enough water to make 1 cup).
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Delicious with vanilla ice cream.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in 3 round 9-inch layer pans at 350° until sides shrink from edges (30 to 35 minutes).

title: margaritas
directions: Mix in blender with at least 1 tray of ice (if this doesn't fill blender, add one more ice cube at a time).
Salt glass rims and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into your unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare according to instructions on the package.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown pork chops slightly in a small amount of fat.
Drain. Place pork chops in baking dish.
On top of each chop, put one onion ring, one pepper ring and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour tomato soup over all. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put eggs into blender, add coconut, butter, nutmeg, sugar, vanilla, flour, salt and milk.
Blend well.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° until well browned.

title: kimchee (pickled cabbage)
directions: Break cabbage apart and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Wash well. Sprinkle liberally with salt and set aside for about 2 hours. Turn cabbage and set aside for another hour.
Rinse and drain. Add salt, Accent, red pepper and garlic to taste.
Add green onions, cut into 2-inch pieces.
Mix as a tossed salad.
Pack in a jar and cover tightly.
Leave space for expansion.
Leave at room temperature for a day, then refrigerate.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomato juice, rice and salt to taste. Stir together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, add cream and cheese.
Very good!

title: squash quiche canoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and then crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Hollow out squash.
If using large squash, half lengthwise first.
Discard seeds and pith; chop remaining portion and saute in bacon fat for 5 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend beaten eggs with heavy cream.
Add cheese, salt, pepper, nutmeg, crumbled bacon and sauteed chopped squash.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water to cover in large saucepan.
Add carrots.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes or until carrots are glazed.

title: breakfast blizzard shake
directions: In blender combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in glass.
Makes one serving.

title: stuffed fillets
directions: Cook the onions in the butter until tender but not brown. Spread each fillet with cooked spinach.
Sprinkle with the onions. Roll up and place in a shallow, buttered baking dish.
Top with the spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, or until fish is flaky when tested with fork.
A nice finish is a dusting of grated cheese over the top, with a minute or two under broiler to melt it a bit.
Serves 4.

title: russian cranberry chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine soup mix, salad dressing and cranberry sauce. Mix well. Place chicken in shallow 2 or 3-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Pour sauce mixture over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer or until chicken is done. Serve over rice. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter candycakes
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Gradually add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend these ingredients into egg mixture. Pour batter into a jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) sprayed with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
While cake is still hot, spread peanut butter evenly over top of cake.
Let cool thoroughly, then spread melted Hershey bar over peanut butter.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: south american chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil.
Put rice, onion, celery and garlic in hot oil; keep turning.
Add remaining ingredients, except peas.
Put into covered roaster and cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 300° oven.
When done, add peas on top.
Serves four.
Serve with salad.

title: braised chicken with potatoes
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, brown chicken in hot oil and margarine until golden brown.
Add onion, potatoes, celery, salt, thyme, pepper, bay leaf and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until chicken and potatoes are almost tender.
Add cut green beans; cover and cook about 10 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add margarine and eggs, one at a time. Add the rest of the ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and blend well. Combine flour and soda.
Add to mixture and blend.
Add nuts and chips.
Blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: donna's chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Chill.
Serve open face on a leaf of lettuce over a sliced croissant roll. Garnish with tomato slice, dill pickle and chips.

title: church windows
directions: Melt butter and chip in big pan.
Let cool so marshmallows won't melt when you mix them in.
Get wax paper and mold mixture into a log.
Put in refrigerator.
Cut when hard.
Cut pieces thin.
You may add walnuts if you want.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Prepare vegetables as directed.
Add teriyaki sauce; let simmer.
Cook chicken strips; add to vegetables.
Serve over rice.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Melt butter in one cup of hot water.
Stir in dry ingredients. Add whole eggs and stir into mix. Add 1/2 cup buttermilk with soda.
This makes a thin batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use your own favorite chocolate icing.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Unroll crescent dough and separate into triangles. Arrange triangles in circle on greased 14 inch pizza pan, with points toward the center and wide ends toward the outside. Pat out dough with fingers to 12 inch circle, pressing seams together to seal.
Bake 13-15 minutes or until golden brown Remove from oven; cool completely.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise and mustard and spread evenly onto crust.
Sprinkle with bacon. Top with lettuce, tomato, cheese and onion. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, cream style and whole kernel corn, sour cream and butter.
Spread in 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes, until knife comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: beef stew with dumplings
directions: *Add two bouillon cubes along with vegetables before pressuring.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients to a soft ball stage (236°).
Cool for 15 minutes; then add vanilla and beat by hand until candy loses its shine.
Add cherries and nuts.
Pour in a glass pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: snicker pie
directions: Bake pie shell as directed and let cool.
Cut up Snickers into 1-inch pieces.
Microwave the Snickers pieces for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir one of the containers of Cool Whip into the melted Snickers. Put the Snickers mixture into the pie shell and cool in the refrigerator.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix well and use for dips.
Good with vegetables or crackers.

title: spinach souffle(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Prepare spinach as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick lasagna
directions: This can be put together the night before and refrigerated without baking.
Increase baking time by 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook bell pepper and onion together until tender. Place chicken back in chicken broth and bring to a boil. Add spaghetti noodles. (The amount of noodles depends on how thick you want it. If it gets too thick, add some water.) Add cooked bell pepper and onion, along with pimento. When noodles are almost done, add desired amount of cheese. Can be served in a casserole or pyrex dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the sugar and flour in double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Stir into flour and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Boil until thick.
Remove from heat.
In 4-quart casserole dish, cover bottom with wafers.
Slice 3 bananas over wafers.
Pour half of pudding over bananas.
Layer once more.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 400° until topping browns.

title: simple shortcake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in buttered casserole dish for 1 hour at 300°.

title: "lynsi's favorite" banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed in large mixing bowl.
Add Eagle Brand milk, sour cream, vanilla and 1/2 container of Cool Whip. Blend together.
Line bowl with wafers and layer pudding mixture with bananas and wafers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and crushed wafers and bananas.
Chill about 1/2 hour to 1 hour before serving.
M-m-good!

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Chill about 2 hours or until firm.
Roll ball in pecans. Serve with crackers and chips.
Yield:
One 5-inch ball.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Lay chicken over rice in single layer.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix water with soup and pour over top. Cover and bake for 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable cheese chowder
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; drain.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in soup and milk.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese on each serving.
Makes 4 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: couscous salad
directions: Bring the water to a boil in a small saucepan.
Pour in the couscous.
Cover the pan and remove from the heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Uncover the pan and stir the couscous right away with a fork.
(If the grains do not separate, fluff them gently with your fingers.)
Transfer the couscous to a bowl and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Season the salad to taste with more lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine Egg Beaters, oil and bananas.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Mix in order and then stir in 4 1/4 cups flour.
Cover with a towel or ventilated lid and place in warm place, free from draft, to rise, no more than 3 to 4 hours.
Early the next morning, divide dough into 3 or 4 well-greased pans (square).
Cover and let rise again for at least 1 hour.
Make holes in the cake dough into which a piece of very cold butter is pressed.
Add light brown sugar to butter holes.
Over all, sprinkle more light brown sugar and bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Let cool. Beat softened cream cheese with 1 cup sugar and then add thawed whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add strawberries.
Mix well and let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese layer and refrigerate until firm.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken a la king(serves 40)
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch squares.
Melt butter.
Blend with flour.
Add cream.
As it thickens, add salt, sugar, pepper, cayenne and curry.
Mix all together.
Add sherry to chicken and cream sauce.

title: chicken bundles
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, milk, dill, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery and onions.
Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 12 rectangles, four from each tube.
Place on a greased baking sheet and press the perforations together.

title: cherry date skillet cookies
directions: In heavy 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat (4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in sugar and dates; remove from heat.
Add egg; return to heat.
Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils all over the top, 4 to 6 minutes. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except 2 1/2 cups coconut.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened (1 to 2 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes; shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. This is a simple salad that keeps well. Better if made a day ahead.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: 1. In a large deep skillet brown chicken and the first
4 cloves of garlic in the olive oil, then remove
chicken.
2. Add the last 2 cloves of garlic, peppers, mushrooms,
celery, onion, oregano, sweet basil, parsley, salt,
pepper, and red pepper (if desired), then brown.
3. Add the whole tomatoes, paste, and chicken. Bring to a
vigorous simmer.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an airtight container.
Put 1/2 cup of mix in a cup and fill with boiling water.
Makes about 1 gallon of dry mix.

title: basic cutlets
directions: If you like veal or pork cutlets, try these turkey cutlets. Just tell your butcher to slice the breast meat appropriately. Again, plan on 4 ounces per person.
Then, when you see a recipe that calls for medallions or cutlets, just switch to turkey.
Of course, you'll also want to find substitutes for the high-fat and high-cholesterol ingredients in such recipes.
Whenever you see "cream" think evaporated skim milk.
Whole eggs convert to egg substitute or egg whites.
Butter, of course, is now synonymous with margarine and then cut the amount in half.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Roll out onto a floured board and cut into biscuits.
Allow to rise 1 to 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Dough keeps well in refrigerator.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, stir well and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain well before serving, or serve with slotted spoon.
Save juice to put leftovers in.
Keeps in refrigerator for a week.

title: bacon dressing for lettuce or endive
directions: Dice bacon and fry lightly.
Take out of grease.
Drain bacon bits.
Let grease cool in pan.
Mix vinegar, water and sugar. Then beat egg with fork in a second small bowl.
Stir liquid mixture into the egg mixture slowly!
Slowly add this mixture to the grease, stirring over low heat until well blended.
Then add bacon and heat all.
If not thick enough, add a small amount of cornstarch.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli and eggs.
Add lemon juice, salt, pepper and just enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Chill.
Top with bacon before serving.

title: soothsayer's sliced apples
directions: Place the chocolate in a double boiler over medium heat until it is almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir and let cool. Spread the nuts in a small bowl.
Dip the apples into the chocolate and shake off excess, then dip the apples into the nuts to coat the bottom.
Set them 3 inches apart on a lightly buttered tray and refrigerate for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour to make a paste.
Add half and half, bouillon cube and seasoned salt; stir until warm.
Add milk; stir until thickened (stir often).
Add Velveeta; when melted, add bay leaf and broccoli.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Mix pudding.
Do not make pudding; use from box with crushed pineapple plus juice.
Let chill at least 2 hours.
Add fruit cocktail (drained) plus Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.
It's a green, light frothy dessert; it's delicious.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Add water, hash browns, frozen vegetables and bouillon. Cook until tender. Stir in cheese, soup and milk.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted. Serve immediately. Can be frozen.

title: zippy dip
directions: In blender or mixer, beat together cottage and cream cheeses, horseradish and Tabasco sauce until smooth and fluffy.
Blend in dill.
Serve in hollowed out cucumber if desired.
Use as a dip for vegetables.

title: mom's chicken almond
directions: Cook chicken breasts in a can of chicken broth.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix together next 7 ingredients.
Stir the chicken into this and put into a casserole.
Top with an additional cup of crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramels
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 30 minutes.
Add cream, boil (stir occasionally) over medium heat until firm ball stage (244° to 248°).
Add 2 cups chopped nuts (chop fine).
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Roll in waxed paper.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Combine and cook the sugar, milk, cinnamon, vinegar and vanilla until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over walnut halves on wax paper.
Separate when cool.
Wonderful for holiday snacks!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, salt and pepper to taste.
Butter casserole dish.
Peel and slice 1/2 of potatoes in dish.
Debone and tear chicken into small pieces.
Place 1/2 on potatoes; add remaining potatoes and then chicken.
Crumble 1 package crackers. Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Melt stick of butter and pour over crackers.
Add paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip fudge bar
directions: Cream the sugar, salt, butter and margarine.
Add the eggs, then the flour and baking powder, which have been sifted together, and the water.
Mix well until smooth.
Add the chocolate chips and mix.
Bake at 360° on greased and floured sheet pans.
(Amount will fill a 17 x 26-inch pan.)

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut off crust of bread and cut into 3/8-inch strips.
Put strips on 2 baking sheets.
Place in a 200° oven for 2 hours to dry out.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour and oleo with beater.
Pack on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Blend in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Smooth cheese mixture over cooled pastry.
Beat instant lemon pudding with 3 cups milk until thick.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: no egg cake(very old recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil water, sugar and raisins together for 20 minutes.
Remove and add butter; let cool.
Add flavoring, cinnamon and allspice.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 9-inch cake pan.
Makes 4 layers.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and salt; add eggs.
Add milk and flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Don't open oven while baking.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in cake at about 1-inch intervals using handle of wooden spoon.
Slowly pour milk into holes.
Pour caramel topping into holes.
Cover with aluminum foil, being careful that it does not touch cake.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Cake is very rich.
Cut and serve.

title: banana cream
directions: Peel bananas.
Rub smooth with the sugar.
Add cream, beaten to a stiff froth.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cold, stir into the jello the banana and cream mixture.

title: bloody marys
directions: Mix all ingredients except vodka and correct seasoning.
Add vodka and pour into a 3-quart container.
Can be kept for a month in refrigerator.
Improves with age.
When ready to serve, pour over ice and add a twist of lime.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salsa suave
directions: Combine ingredients, except chiles and simmer 10 minutes to reduce some of the excess liquid.
Add chiles and simmer 10 to 15 minutes more.
(Use a 5-quart open saute pan as it allows the liquid to reduce quickly without overcooking the ingredients.)
Makes one quart.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on platter.
Cover with tomato sauce, green chilies, chopped onion and fresh chopped tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese, then sliced black olives.
You can add anything else you want.
You can substitute the cream cheese with refried beans or jalapeno bean dip.
Arrange chips around dip.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine oleo, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir together until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pat mixture into bottom of well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs lightly, then beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in jelly roll pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cool pan on wire rack to room temperature.
Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package using 1/2 cup less water. Add vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add the jello mixture to the mayonnaise, a little at a time, stirring well to keep smooth (or use beater).
When completely blended, add cucumbers.
Pour into mold and chill.
Unmold and garnish.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add the powdered sugar.
Fold in the whipped topping and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix the pudding, milk and vanilla.
Stir the two mixtures together and pour over the cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle the remaining cookie crumbs over the top.
Freeze overnight or until served.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; put in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and oleo to crumble stage.
Place on top of rhubarb and put in microwave for another 6 to 8 minutes.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.
Form into balls.
Place about 1/4 inch apart in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour strained soup over meatballs.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes, depending on size of meatballs.
Serve with happiness.

title: cremish
directions: In medium saucepan, mix together milk, egg yolks, cornstarch, sugar and vanilla sugar.
Heat and stir with whisk until thickened. Cool completely.
When butter and cooked mixture are at room temperature, beat butter until creamy.
Add cooked mixture by tablespoon while beating until all the cooked mixture is in with the butter.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Sprinkle the soda over beans.
Boil for 10 minutes, skimming off foam.
Drain 1/2 water off; cover with warm water.
Add 3/4 cup sugar per pound of beans.
Add diced ham or bacon, the molasses, diced onion, ginger, salt and pepper. Bake at 300° for 8 hours, or use slow cooker.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour to the mixture and beat until smooth.
Add lemon extract and mix well.
Fold in 7 ounces of 7-Up.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (35 minutes in glass).
Cover while warm with topping.

title: coated pecans
directions: Whip egg white and add slowly the brown sugar mixed with flour.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring, then fold in pecans.
Lay on a greased pan and bake at 250° for 45 minutes or less.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Combine soups, rice and mushrooms.
Season pork as usual. Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Heat all together in large coffeepot or on stove.
You may substitute frozen orange juice and ReaLemon for the fruit juices. Serve hot.

title: eileen's pineapple bars
directions: Boil glaze and stir. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from oven and spread glaze.

title: double crust apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in medium saucepan.
Blend with 2 cups of water.
Cook slowly until boils, stirring constantly.
Add butter to boiling water mixture.
Add diced apples.
Cook until very soft.
Add flavorings and spices.
Pour ingredients into unbaked pie shell; cover with unbaked pie shell, sealing edges with fork and making small slits in the top pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, until crusts (bottom and top) are golden brown.

title: easy peach crisp for two
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Add granola, brown sugar and cinnamon; mix well, then remove from heat.
Divide peaches between two 1/2-cup ramekins or other small, ovenproof dishes.
Sprinkle half of the granola mixture over each.
Bake 15 minutes until hot and browned.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: chinese chews
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored and add sugar gradually.
Add the three dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Add vanilla and fold in dates and nuts.
Fold in the 3 egg whites which have beaten stiff.
Bake in a (9 x 13-inch) pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: cheese blitz
directions: Mix together the cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Cut the edges off of bread and mash flat.
Spread cheese mixture on bread and roll it up and dip in melted butter.
Then roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Cook the rice in a pot with 2 1/2 cups of water.
Add salt and cook until rice is tender.
Add can of evaporated milk plus 1/2 can of hot water to the cooked rice.
Add sugar, raisins, vanilla and cinnamon and the 2 egg yolks that have been slightly beaten.
Beat the egg whites with a heaping teaspoonful of sugar until stiff.
Add them to the pudding.
Put the rice pudding into a bowl that has been greased and put the bowl in a pan of hot water.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
You can also use 4 small aluminum pans.

title: pumpkin jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar and pumpkin to beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to egg mixture.
Grease an 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Pat dough in pan and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well. Place wax paper on cookie sheet (9 x 13). Place batter onto wax paper. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. While baking, sprinkle powdered sugar over dish towel. Place upside down on towel and roll towel. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.

Cut potatoes into quarters (about 1 1/2 potatoes per person). Place potatoes in a shallow baking pan and sprinkle with rosemary, salt, pepper and garlic powder, then dribble the olive oil over potatoes and shake pan to coat potatoes.
Place pan in a 500° oven for about 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 450° and continue to cook for 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
About 5 minutes before potatoes are finished cooking, place sliced garlic in pan. Serve hot.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix salad dressing, potatoes, cheese, soup, onion and pepper.
Spoon into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with combined corn flakes and margarine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes; pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork in a few places.
Bake potatoes on a rack at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Cut a thin slice from top of each potato. Scoop out the pulp into a bowl.
Mash the potato pulp with the hot milk or half and half until fluffy.
Beat in the butter and the green onions.
Add seasonings.
Fry the bacon until crisp. Crumble; add to potato mixture.
Spoon potato mixture into shells. Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Place potatoes on baking sheet. Bake at 375° until potatoes are piping hot and cheese is melted, about 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pat each biscuit into a 4-inch circle; put each biscuit onto a greased baking sheet.
