Mix tomato sauce and oregano in a measuring cup; spoon some on each biscuit.
Put pepperoni on top of the mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheese, then bake about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot peppers
directions: Bring mixture to boil and pour over hot peppers packed in sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with graham crackers (do not crush).
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture on graham crackers.
Add second layer of graham crackers; pour remaining mixture over.
Add another layer of grahams.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: cheesy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To cook chicken:
Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste, place in a microwave-safe dish, cover and cook in microwave for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn and cook another 2 to 3 minutes or until cooked through and no longer pink inside.
Let cool.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, combine chicken, rice and soup and mix well.
Top with cheese, then with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly and bread is crunchy.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook chicken in broth (add water to cover) and oil. Cook, covered, 30 minutes.
Drain chicken.
Save broth.
Cut chicken in long pieces. Cook noodles and drain.

title: bubble bread
directions: Cube the thawed bread and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix all other ingredients well and pour over cubes. Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pat over bottom and sides of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, cream cheese, sugar and milk in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed for 30 minutes or until very smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Top with mixture of confectioners sugar and sour cream.
Bake for 5 minutes longer. Yield:
12 servings.

title: southern pralines
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan over medium heat, bring brown sugar, cream, corn syrup, and salt to a boil.
Stir constantly. Cook until a candy thermometer reads 234° (soft ball stage).
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat, add butter but do not stir.
Cool to 150°, about 35 minutes.
Stir in the pecans and vanilla.
Stir with a wooden spoon until candy just begins to thicken but is still glossy, about 5-7 minutes.
Quickly drop by heaping teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Spread to form 2-inch patties.
Store in an airtight container.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Pull apart artichoke hearts; drain and rinse.
Mix together mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Add to artichoke hearts.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Melt cheese over boiling water.
Combine other ingredients and whirl in blender.
Combine both mixtures and heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.

title: 7-up refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine 7-Up and 100% bran cereal in a small bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Combine flours, all-bran cereal, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine sugars and shortening in a large mixing bowl; beat well.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Stir in buttermilk and 7-Up mixture.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Cook celery and onion in small amount broth from chicken until tender.
Mix all ingredients except cheese in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese just before serving.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off excess grease.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and simmer.
You may use additional seasoning.
Place in large casserole and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes before removing.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cover rhubarb with boiling water for 10 minutes and drain. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and then combine with rhubarb.
Pour into crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: In
a large bowl, stir sugar into crushed strawberries; set aside.
Measure
3/4 cup water; mix with Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil;
boil hard for 1 full minute, stirring constantly. Add to fruit, stirring to dissolve sugar, for 3 full minutes. Ladle into jars;
cover and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours,
then place in freezer.
Make 1 batch at a time.	Do not attempt to make double recipes.
Recipe makes approximately 42 ounces of preserves (five 8-ounce jars).

title: elegant oysters
directions: Drain oysters thoroughly.
Spread 3/4 cup onion in well-greased dish.
Cover with oysters.
Pour half and half over top.
Combine remaining onions and cheese; sprinkle over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add zucchini, sugar, oil and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread onto greased and floured 8 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can frost with chocolate frosting, if desired.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together cream cheese and minced onion.
Spread mixture evenly on ham slices, using approximately 2 tablespoons per slice. Roll slices.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Cut slices into desired size.
Makes about 48 pieces.

title: pupu chicken
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients until sugar is dissolved at a low boil.
Add green onion, finely minced, and set aside.
Roll chicken wings in flour and fry until done.
Dip wings in sauce. Serve hot or cold.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut in bottom of well-greased 15 x 11 x 2-inch pan. Spread pecans over coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed; pour over top of coconut and nuts.
Mix softened oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on cake; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Saute onions in butter along with minced garlic and chopped green pepper.
Add tomatoes (chopped in 1/2-inch cubes).
Add curry powder and milk.
Simmer until mixture thickens, don't boil. Add shrimp and mayonnaise.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 7 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken in olive sauce
directions: Cut 4 thin slices lemon, squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon, set aside.
Flatten chicken to even thickness. In hot oil, cook chicken until brown on both sides.
In bowl, combine soup and milk and stir in olives, juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken, top with lemon slices.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: play clay(for the kids on a rainy day)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Stir this into 7 cups of boiling water. Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Cool in a covered dish.
Add coloring.

title: shanghai beef
directions: Saute beef in oil.
Add cornstarch and stir in broth, water chestnuts, green pepper and onion. Add soy sauce and pepper. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and let stand 5 minutes; fluff and serve.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Pack beans lengthwise into clean jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
To each jar add garlic, dill and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over beans, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: biloxi(batter fried shrimp)
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving the last section of shell and tail intact.
Butterfly shrimp by cutting along outside curve almost through.
Remove vein, flatten shrimp and set aside.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and milk in a bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Hold cupcakes, top side down, in palm of hand.
Spread whipped topping mixture on bottom and sides.
Press coconut onto frosting.
Place cupcakes, top side down, on serving platter. Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Store any leftover dessert in refrigerator.
Makes 24.

title: crunchy party mix
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, garlic salt, salt and pepper sauce.
Keep warm.
tags: bite size crispy rice square cereal

title: gloucestershire pie
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Put onions and apples in a pan and cover with water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Meanwhile boil swede for 10 minutes, then add potato and cook until both are soft.
Drain well and mash together until smooth.
Grease an ovenproof dish with the butter.
Place layers of meat, onion and apple in the dish, seasoning and sprinkling each layer with herbs as you fill up the dish.
Pour in the gravy and top with the mashed potato and swede mixture.
Dot top with butter and bake uncovered for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Serve with a green vegetable. Serves 4.

title: crab n' cream cheese
directions: Place the cream cheese in center of nice serving plate.
Drain the crab meat and spread over cream cheese and over sides.
Top with cocktail sauce.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion, garlic and Italian seasoning until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli; cook until tender and liquid evaporates.
Remove from heat; stir in soup, cheese and egg.
Set filling aside.

title: eula's chicken gumbo
directions: Place chicken in a large pot with water to cover.
Bring to boil and cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from pot; discard bones and skin.
Return meat to pot.
Add next 8 ingredients and add 3 quarts water.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and cook approximately 1 hour (vegetables should be very tender).
Brown flour until dark brown in enough drippings or oil to moisten.
(An iron skillet is best for this.)
Add enough broth from pot to brown flour in skillet to make smooth thick gravy. Add gravy to pot.
Add salt and pepper if needed.
Cover and simmer a few minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place dill, garlic and hot pepper in a quart jar.
Wash cucumbers and pack in jars.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil. Pour this mixture over cucumbers and seal jars.
Allow at least 8 weeks to cure.

title: rosy pickled eggs
directions: In large bowl combine water, beet liquid and vinegar.
Add sugar, pickling spices, bay leaf, salt and garlic.
Mix well.
Add eggs and onion rings.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Pour oil and margarine into skillet and heat slow.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Chop celery and onions into small pieces. Add to oil and margarine mixture; simmer about 5 minutes.
Add hamburger and fry until browned.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break pretzels and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks butter and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Pour over pretzels.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°; let cool, then break up with knife.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, drained pineapple
and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Mix strawberry Jell-O and 2 cups hot water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Allow to jell slightly and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate. Lasts up to a week.

title: anne brown's christmas ribbon salad
directions: Make lime jello according to directions on package.
Pour 3/4-inch layer in loaf pan and let stand until hard.

title: ranchero potatoes
directions: Cook in cast-iron skillet, uncovered, until tender, stirring often.
Add picante sauce and simmer 5 minutes; serve hot.

title: chocolate chip cream bars
directions: Slice one roll of cookies; spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cookies.
Cut second roll of cookies and spread evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked scalloped corn
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: tomato juice punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Strain and cool. Serve over ice.

title: callas
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add cold water; beat 3 minutes.
Drop by tablespoon on a greased and floured tin.
Bake until light brown.
While still hot, roll into shape of cornucopia and tie with string to keep shape.
When cold, fill with sweetened and flavored whipped cream.
Decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: pecan oat waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend in blender.
Pour into hot waffle iron.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Combine all vegetables and spices and mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft batter.
Spoon batter into hot oil in frying pan to make the fritters.
Serve hot.
You can use very ripe or still a little green tomatoes in this recipe.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili sauce and jelly.
Roll into bite-size balls and brown on all sides.
Mix chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meatballs and simmer 45 minutes.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Heat raspberries with 1/2 cup water, sugar and lemon juice. Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir into raspberry mixture.
Cook until thickened and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: basic pralines by harry
directions: Lightly coat wax paper with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine sugars, butter, milk and chopped pecans in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil uncovered 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly or until candy thermometer reaches 220°.
Remove saucepan from heat and beat 4 to 6 minutes with a wooden spoon or just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tablespoon onto prepared wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: paella
directions: Cook garlic and butter in 2 1/2 quart microwave-safe dish on High for 1 minute.
Blend cornstarch with broth and add with remaining ingredients to garlic mixture.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir twice and fluff with fork.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Chill at least two hours.
Add cherry topping.

title: reuben soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add broth and baking soda.
Combine cornstarch and water; add to pan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Add sauerkraut, cream and corned beef; simmer and stir for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and heat until melted. Add salt and pepper.
Garnish with croutons if desired.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: deluxe corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream, oil and corn.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and 2 Tbsp. sugar together until yeast is frothy.
Beat eggs.
Add yeast mixture to eggs plus vegetable oil, sugar, salt, and water; mix well.
Add in flour.
Knead and add up to 1/2 c. of flour if necessary.
Dough will be sticky. Once dough has been kneaded, let rise until it doubles, approximately 2 hours.
Melt butter and pour into 2 bundt pans. Roll dough out to 1/2 inch thickness and cut out circles with a glass (2 to 3 inches in diameter).
Arrange circles of dough in bundt pans.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes and then bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: julia's blueberry cream pie
directions: Cream the first three ingredients together.
Whip 1 cup of whipping cream, fold into cheese mixture (may have to beat together to incorporate better).
Set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes with sauerkraut
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise together and pour over potatoes, hot dogs and sauerkraut.
Add butter or oleo on top, if desired.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except the peanut butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Then cook to soft boil stage (test small amount in cold water to get ball stage).

title: baked french toast
directions: Butter oblong cake pan.
Arrange bread slices to fill pan. In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, cream, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over bread slices.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour, then serve.

title: egg yolk paint for sugar cookies
directions: Add food coloring to yolks. "Paint" before baking. Two yolks divided into 4 cups is usually enough to paint one batch of cookies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a full boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then add remaining ingredients. Blend with hot mixture until it begins to thicken.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.
They become hard as they cool.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Save fruit juices to add to punch or Kool-Aid.

title: baked chicken dish
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients except for the potato chips. Place in a 3-quart, oblong, glass dish and top with the potato chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into greased 9 x 13 pan. Pour pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Sprinkle nuts over cake. Cut butter into pats and place on top of nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: savannah's tea
directions: Boil water for tea and take off burner.
Put Luzianne tea bags into water.
Let sit 20 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar into pitcher.
Add tea and then fill with tap or bottled water. Stir well. Let sit for 1 hour before putting into refrigerator. Delicious!

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in a 2-quart baking dish. Top with strips of bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: once-a-year coconut butter creams
directions: Combine the above ingredients and chill. Form into balls. Chill again. In top of double boiler, melt 2 large packages chocolate chips (or approximately 1 1/2 pounds of melting chocolate and 3/4 pound block paraffin; paraffin optional). Dip balls in chocolate with toothpicks and set on waxed paper to set.

title: macaroni cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Add shredded cheese, mixing well.
Stir in the cooked macaroni.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder. Cut in margarine and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in egg whites, mixing until flour is moistened. Press 1/2 of dough into greased 9 x 13 pan. Spread jelly over dough. Crumble remaining dough over jelly. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are firm and dry. Cool. Cut into bars. Freezes well.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, potato chips, nuts and flour; mix well.
Form into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Dip bottom of a glass in sugar and flatten cookies.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake crust and set aside to cool.
Mix the ingredients and cook until thick; set aside to cool.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix together and bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: hamburger supreme by danish
directions: Combine ground beef, onions, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well and shape into patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides in hot vegetable oil.
Remove patties when brown and pour off all but 3 to 4 tablespoons of fat.
Add flour to fat (may add some salt and pepper, if desired).
Mix well.
Add milk and mushroom soup; stir until thick.
Return patties to pan and cook 15 minutes longer, or place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil hen until very tender.
Skin and bone.
Skim most of grease off liquid, then cook pork and onion in it.
Meanwhile, cook cut up potatoes and tomatoes together, being careful not to let potatoes scorch.
When all done, combine all ingredients together in large pot.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Allow to simmer gently for several hours until the consistency of thick soup.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Freezes well.

title: kenyan stew
directions: Chop vegetables. Place potatoes and carrots in water to prevent darkening. Heat oil in pan which soup will be cooked. Fry onions until brown. Add tomatoes and cook on medium until tender. Add potatoes and carrots (remove from water) to onions and tomatoes. Add water, salt, chili powder and any optional ingredients desired. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve with chapatis or Ugali.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix together oil, eggs and carrots.
Add dry ingredients into oil mixture.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze until ready to use.
Add ginger ale to partially thawed mixture before serving. Serves 50.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, salt and orange rind and beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately.
When well mixed, put half of batter in 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
To remainder of batter, add 3 tablespoons of cocoa and 1/4 teaspoon soda dissolved in just enough hot water to make a paste.
Put in pans with first and bake.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the ingredients 1 1/2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon butter.
Mix well and pour over large bowl of popcorn.
Stir well and cool.

title: shrimp and wild rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add seasonings, rice, soup and water.
Fold in shrimp.
Bake in baking dish 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Beat the cream cheese and preserves in a mixing bowl with an electric mixer until well blended. Stir in the pineapple. Place the peach halves cut side up on a lettuce-lined platter. Fill each half with some of the cream cheese mixture. Garnish with fresh mint if desired. Serves about 15.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss ingredients together (except bacon).
Add dressing and toss.
Top with bacon.

title: cardamom print wafers
directions: Stir together flour, cardamom, cinnamon and salt.
In a small mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Stir in flour mixture until well mixed.
Cover and chill about 2 hours or until easy to handle.

title: fried rice
directions: In a large frypan, melt butter and saute ginger and garlic. Add pork and saute until well done.
Add shrimp and saute until tender.
Stir in scallions and rice.
Cook until heated through. Add seasonings.
Make hole in center of rice.
Crack eggs into hole.
Beat until partially cooked.
Stir-fry into rice until well cooked and mixed.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim broccoli and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Steam in salted water until tender.
Saute onions, celery and garlic in butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, broth and herbs.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Add broccoli, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with almonds and chopped tomatoes.

title: daphne's coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar together well.
Add oleo (cut into flour mix).
Add the dissolved yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and egg yolks.
Mix all this well and add to flour mixture with warm milk. Cover and leave overnight in refrigerator.
Divide into 3 balls. Roll out in oval shape 1/4-inch thick.
Spread filling on half and fold over.
Pinch edges.
Put on greased cookie sheet.

title: jollof rice
directions: Put oil in big pot over medium heat; add chicken, spareribs, ham, shrimp and onions.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and allspice and saute until lightly browned.
Drain tomatoes (save liquid); add to meat whole tomatoes, tomato sauce and vegetables.
Cover and steam about 15 minutes.
Add water and
tomato juice and cook until meat is tender.
In separate pot, boil rice for 10 minutes. Drain and add to other ingredients.
Simmer over low heat until done, stirring occasionally.
Serve on platter, garnished with lettuce leaves, hard-boiled eggs and pepper rings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Melt butter; let cool.
Cream in sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add 1 cup buttermilk; add soda to the 1/3 cup buttermilk.
Chop nuts and cut dates and orange slice candy. Mix these with 1 cup flour; add remainder of flour to butter mixture.
Add dates, candy slices and coconut to batter.
Bake in a tube pan (10-inch), well-greased and floured.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Mix milk and juice.
Fold in pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill.
Better if made the day before serving.

title: ice cream(kid's recipes)
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in small coffee can.
Tape lid onto can.
Place small can inside large coffee can.
Fill space with ice and rock salt.
Put lid on large can.
Roll can between two children (4-5 feet apart) for ten minutes.
Pour off water and fill can with more ice and salt.
Roll for ten more minutes.
This can be flavored with other extracts, peppermint is especially nice, but try almond, maple, etc.
Yields 2 cups.

title: cocoa frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, mix nonfat dry milk in water until dissolved.
Over medium heat, stir in sifted unsweetened cocoa powder and honey.
Cook and stir for 15 to 20 minutes, until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Let cool 10 minutes, and frosting is ready to use.
Frosting will continue to harden as it cools.

title: cyclone chili
directions: Cook meat, onions, peppers and garlic until meat turns gray. Add remaining ingredients and cook 3 to 4 hours.
Add water if necessary.
Let cool.
Reheat and serve with chopped onions and shredded Cheddar cheese for toppings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion and mushrooms lightly in margarine in skillet. Add broccoli and simmer 15 minutes.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Great for microwave; use 70% setting for about 10 minutes.)

title: lucille stock's banana cake
directions: Melt butter and stir in frosting and oatmeal.
In another bowl, beat eggs, bananas and sour cream.
Then add cake mix. Layer frosting mix and cake mix dough 3 times each, with frosting on top.
Use greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Pull out tube with cake on it and continue to cool.
Then turn out on plate top up.

title: radish relish
directions: Put radishes in blender; cover with water.
Blend at high speed about 3 seconds, until radishes are chopped.
Pour in a colander; sprinkle with salt and mix.
Allow to drain 1/2 hour. In a bowl, mix radishes, sour cream, vinegar, chives and pepper. Refrigerate.
Yields 2 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook elbows according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Combine cooled elbows with remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Cover and chill. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: raisin energy cookies
directions: Combine raisins, apricots, dry milk, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix.
Stir in flour and wheat germ.
Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and liquid milk.
Combine with dry mixture and add oats and sunflower seeds. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Stir in syrup, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla. Mix well. Add raisins and nuts. Pour in pie shell and top with second pie shell. Pinch edges together and cut slits in top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding, milk, sour cream and whipped topping until smooth.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer wafers, bananas and pudding, making two layers.
Top with more whipped topping.

title: special chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Batter
should
be
very thin.
Coffee and water increase moistness.
This cake does not have a mocha or coffee flavor!
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately until well mixed.
Add dates, orange slices and nuts.

Bake in Bundt or tube pan for 2 hours in 275° oven. When done, remove from oven and punch holes in top of cake while still warm in pan and pour over the cake 1/2 cup orange juice and 1 cup brown sugar.
Let cool; remove from pan.
Can be wrapped in foil and frozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with roll dough; press seams to seal.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer sausage and cheese in prepared dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl; mix until smooth.
Pour over layers. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Blend ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9
x
13-inch
pan.
(Tube
pan for 1 hour.) Glaze.

title: basic flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients (if you want large tortillas omit the baking powder).
Work in shortening and mix well.
Add the water and knead until dough is springy (you might need a little more or less water, depending on how pliable the dough is).

title: cherry pineapple bars
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, flour and salt.
Mix until crumbly.
Press about 3/4 of the crumb mixture on bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain canned fruits.
Reserve liquids and place fruit in refrigerator in bowl.
Dissolve jellos in boiling water.
Add 1 cup of liquid from fruits to dissolve jello; stir.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch glass pan and refrigerate until slightly jelled.
Fold in fruits.
Refrigerate until completely jelled.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well; fold in pecans. Spread over jello.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Mix
first 4 ingredients in large pot and dissolve over low heat
to
keep candy from burning.	Turn off burner.
Add juices. Store
as
is
and	dilute	as
desired.
Recommended dilution: 1/4 cup water to 3/4 cup tea.
Serve hot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together skim milk, melted margarine, egg whites and fructose and pour over bread.
Add cinnamon and vanilla to taste. Add raisins. Bake in muffin pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: plum dumplings
directions: Pit prune plums.
Place 1 sugar cube inside pitted plum.
Set aside.
Mix flour, dry cottage cheese, butter and salt, beating until smooth.
Chill dough.
Divide dough into 12 portions.
Wrap dough around plum, sealing!
Cook in boiling water (salted) 10 minutes with cover.
Drain.

title: pineapple slices
directions: Beat and frost, then cut in squares.

title: beet and horseradish mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients. Slightly oil the mold and pour mixture in.
Chill in refrigerator until formed.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Strain and set aside.
Melt cheese and soup together.
Mix well.
Add shrimp and rice to the cheese and soup mix.
Mix all together.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for about 1/2 hour. Should be golden brown at the edges.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients until smooth. Spread on crust.
Put a layer of chocolate pudding.
Put a layer of vanilla pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: viola's corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper until well blended.
Pour over vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Cover tightly and marinate overnight.

title: apple-orange nut bread
directions: Mix and bake in 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Spray and fill 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook Shells as directed.
Mix Chicken, stuffing and mayonnaise.
After shells are cool enough to handle, stuff them with the chicken mixture and place in a greased casserole.
Mix soup and water and pour over shells.
Bake at 325 for 1/2 hour. Makes about 20 shells.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat milk and limeade together and fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Top with more Cool Whip, if desired.

title: corn scallop
directions: Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, then add milk, egg yolks and vanilla. Cook until thick and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown in oven.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into the bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: tofu chili
directions: Reserve the cooking water or liquid from cans of pintos.
Mix the soy sauce with next 6 ingredients (including the first of 2 tablespoons of oil); coat tofu pieces with this mixture.
Fry over medium heat until all liquid is absorbed and tofu is browned. Saute the green pepper, onions and garlic in the other 2 tablespoons oil.
Put beans, tofu mixture and sauteed vegetables in a cooking pot or crockpot.
Add the tomatoes, sauce and season. Simmer 30 minutes or longer.
If in crock-pot, simmer several hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: green beans
directions: Cook beans as directed.
Drain.
Make sauce with butter, flour, salt, pepper, sour cream and cheese.
Add beans to this mixture and top with crushed corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, salt and softened butter well, until sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Add milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake for 7 minutes at 425°. Lower heat to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes until it simmers.

title: colonial peanut and chestnut soup
directions: Combine flour and margarine to make a roux.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Simmer on low. Garnish with chopped peanuts and water chestnuts.

title: easy cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream ingredients together until fluffy.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker pie crust.
Pour the cherry pie filling over the top.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and oleo thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs slowly to sugar mix.
Add the nuts.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and add to the sugar and egg mixture. Shape into 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
(These rolls freeze very well.) Slice thin and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until golden.

title: herbed potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions together until tender.
Drain; save potato water.
Put potatoes through coarse strainer.
While potatoes cook, melt butter in 6-quart saucepan.
Add parsley and basil.
Blend flour, salt and pepper in, gradually add the cold milk.
Add scalded milk and potato water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in potatoes and onions.
Serve with chopped parsley and dust with paprika.
Makes 12 cups.
This soup freezes successfully.

title: ona chapman's coffee frappe
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot coffee and cool. Add 1 pint of whipped cream. When ready to serve, add 6 to 8 quarts vanilla ice cream.

title: oven jambalaya
directions: In a 3-quart casserole combine the rice, stock, salsa, onions, garlic, salt, peas, oregano and coriander.
Stir to combine.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut onion in rounds.
Dice bell pepper.
Add onion and pepper to a frying pan or saute pan. Heat with vegetable oil. Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Stir-fry until chicken is completely cooked. Serve with pepper and onion surrounding chicken.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and vanilla.
Chill dough 1 hour before baking.
Roll out for cutouts. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: doritos chicken casserole
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix and heat in a pan.
Pour rest over layers in casserole and sprinkle 1/2 c. of the cheese over top.
Cover with foil and bake 350° for 30 minutes

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Do not dissolve jello but add to other ingredients dry.
Other flavors jello may be used, if desired.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Mix milk, grated cheese, vinegar and dry mustard.
Mix well. Use for sandwiches.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo.
Remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar while hot.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch bake pan.
Freeze 20 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before cutting.
Can't fail.

title: pecan petit fours
directions: Beat 2 cups of the butter and the 1 cup of granulated sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until thoroughly blended.
Add flour and beat on low speed just until dough comes together.
Gather dough into a ball; flatten slightly.
Refrigerate, wrapped in plastic, for 2 hours.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: In
large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed and
dry yeast.
In saucepan, heat cottage cheese, water and butter
until
mixture
is
very
warm.
Add
egg and warm liquid to
flour
mixture.
Blend at lowest speed on electric mixer until
moistened.
Beat
3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in
remaining 1 1/2 to 3 cups flour to form a stiff dough.
Cover and
let
rise
in
warm
place until light and doubled
in
size (approximately
hour).
Stir down dough. Turn
into well-greased
2 quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cook sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in saucepan, stirring constantly, until it bubbles.
Cook for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
Place corn in
a large roaster pan.
Pour syrup over and stir well.
Place in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking.
Remove from oven and cool.
Separate while cooling.
Many servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip until you don't see any white.
Put in crust and chill for 4 hours or more.

title: boudin sandwiches
directions: Chop ham in blender or food processor (do not overchop or will be mushy).
Mix in large bowl with chopped eggs and remaining ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise for good spreading consistency.
Can be kept in sealed container in refrigerator for several days.

title: tuna swirl pot pie
directions: Combine soup, onion, parsley and poultry seasoning in baking dish.
Blend well.
Add tuna, pimientos and peas to soup mixture. Mix gently.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Place biscuits on tuna mixture in slightly overlapping border.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	for
5	minutes;
drain.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise,
mushroom
soup and grated onion; mix well.
Place in a greased casserole; sprinkle with cracker crumbs.	Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hershey's fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla in large bowl. Combine sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan; boil 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour boiling mixture over the mixture in the bowl.
Stir until butter and chips melt.
Beat with electric mixer until it begins to thicken.
Pour into pan and let set for 4 to 6 hours.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2-quart shallow ovenproof baking dish.
Mix all ingredients in casserole until blended. (Wrap and refrigerate at this point if making ahead.)
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Combine ingredients and stir often with tenderness.
Sprinkle freely with kindness and serve daily to your family.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of pan or dish.
Mix the Dream Whip as directed on box. Add the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour on crust and chill.
Top with your favorite pie filling.
(Chill can as you chill above).
Place in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving. This will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Cook ground chuck in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe pan drippings from skillet with a paper towel. Return ground chuck to skillet and add tomato sauce, sliced carrots, chopped onion and undrained, sliced mushrooms.
Stir in water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until carrots are tender, stirring occasionally. Serve hot.
Yields 10 servings (1 cup each).
Calories:
84. Exchanges:
1 starch.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Select a fine, ripe melon.
Cut in eighths and cut out fruit. Pare green and all the pink from rind.
Cut the green part into thin slices, then in strips or rounds.
Measure 7 cups.
Cover with cold water and salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain; cover with fresh water.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine boiling water, vinegar, sugar, powdered cinnamon and cloves in enamel pan.
Tie whole spices in small cheesecloth bag and add to pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all but butter and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake a while, then add butter over top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: soft peach ice cream
directions: Chill 2 small stemmed dessert or wine glasses.
Peel and pit peaches, slice into blender container.
Place ice cream on top, dribble in almond flavoring.
Let sit in refrigerator during meal. When ready to serve blend just long enough to combine thoroughly, scrapping down as necessary.

title: pineapple snowball cake
directions: Dissolve plain gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water, pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Mix well; refrigerate until cool.
When partly jelled, add Dream Whip.
Mix well.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 11 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pot pie i
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boil; stir constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and veggies.
Put into pie shell and put top crust on; slit top.
Roll ends under.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great with turkey leftover meat also.

title: swiss cheese fondue
directions: *You can use half Swiss cheese and half Gruyere cheese, it is very tasty.

title: christmas salad
directions: Place frozen strawberries into bowl while frozen; add sugar and let thaw, then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add bananas before serving.
Beautiful in a clear glass bowl.

title: crabmeat dip the easy way
directions: Combine all in crock-pot on low heat, stirring to mix occasionally to blend ingredients.
Serve with soda crackers or cut up vegetables.

title: green bean mushroom casserole(large crowd)
directions: In a large container, stir soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Mix in beans and 4 cans of onions.
Use 3 baking dishes, 12 x 8 x 2-inches or 2 baking dishes, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbling. Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 50 (1/2 cup) servings.
Very tasty!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pour into pan.
Put a little ketchup on top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: apple-nut bread
directions: Mix together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar. On low speed, add oil, eggs, chopped apples and nuts.
Bake in two medium-sized pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with apple butter, honey or cream cheese.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk until freezer is 2/3 full.
Freeze.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, salt, egg, chocolate and water. Add flour and nuts.
Spray pan with Pam and cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas cake
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients and let come to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Pour over cake as soon as you take it out of the oven. Let stay in pan until cool.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: angel food jello cake
directions: Mix jello and water and let cool.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, coconut and Cool Whip.
Line Bundt pan or angel cake pan with plastic wrap.
Pour in half of jello mixture, then broken pieces of cake.
Top with rest of jello mixture.
Press down firmly.
Chill well.
Invert on plate.

title: donuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add salt and eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add nutmeg, flour and baking powder.
Mix until well blended.
Put half on floured board at a time and roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with donut cutter and drop in hot shortening.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Drain on paper towels in long pan or dish.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon and 2 tablespoons flour for topping.
Mix first four ingredients like pie crust.
Beat egg and milk lightly and add to dry mixture; mix well.
Peel and slice apples and place on top of batter which has been placed in two 7 x 9-inch pans. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake for about 25 minutes in 375° oven or until apples are soft.

title: halibut elly's
directions: Slice halibut into fillets 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick; put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour wine over fish; let set 1/2 hour. Slice onion very thin and scatter over fish.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together; spread on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until fish is just set.
Do not overcook.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Combine water, 1 1/2 C. sugar, and the cream of tartar in a pot.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add crackers, do not stir.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix everything together, except butter. Cut butter in 8 slices and place on top. Put in microwave on 2 or 3 minutes, depending on microwave. Stir and pour in dish until firm, then cut in squares.

title: waldorf grape salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients.
Whip cream.
Add remaining ingredients except lettuce and blend well.
Fold dressing into salad; serve cold on lettuce cups.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: In large saucepan, bring about 1 1/2-inches of water to a boil.
Place the cauliflower in a steamer basket and set basket in the saucepan.
Cover and steam for 6 to 8 minutes, until crisp-tender.

title: mock chicken
directions: Combine meats, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well and form into patties. Brown well.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Bake in a 250° to 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: loren's hot spiced apple cider
directions: Mix all juices in pot or crock-pot.
Put all spices in cheesecloth.
Tie together with string.
Add to juice.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes before serving.
Turn heat to low and enjoy the entire day!
Great for a cool Fall day!!!

title: cream cheese monkey
directions: Cut biscuits in half; flatten on lightly floured surface. Place cream cheese cubes on each.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Fold biscuits to enclose filling, sealing edges.
Heat margarine, brown sugar and syrup in saucepan until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Layer brown sugar mixture and biscuits alternately in greased Bundt pan until all ingredients are used. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 3 minutes.

title: mexican pot roast(makes 6 to 8 large servings)
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot and cover with water.
Cook slowly for 7 to 9 hours.
Keep covered with water and stir occasionally during cooking.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 to 3 tablespoons of picante sauce.
Meat will shred.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Don't forget to grease the pan.

title: apple graham crisp
directions: Put apple into individual serving dish.
Crush graham over apple slices that were mixed with sweetener and cinnamon.
Add 1 teaspoon of butter or low-fat margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: anise toast
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs and add one at a time. Beat in the anise flavoring.
Sift and stir in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Form into 3 loaves on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Slice and turn on one side. Bake 8 minutes.
Turn onto other side.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all together, cover and chill.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry-raspberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and stir well until melted.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour into pan or mold.
Chill until firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Add sausage and Bisquick.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen and baked as needed.

title: upside-down chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Grease pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Pour in pan.
In a bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Spoon drop over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chocolate fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan.
Mix cake mix, whiskey, sour cream and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except corn syrup.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 20 minutes. Remove from pan.
When cake is completely cool, wrap tightly and refrigerate.
Brush with warm corn syrup before serving.
Slice thin.
Keeps 2 weeks, refrigerated.

title: ranch style biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set 30 minutes before cooking.
You can keep this in refrigerator as long as two weeks.
Pinch off and cook as you want to.
(Don't overknead your dough.)
Bake in 400° oven.
Very good.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in stewed tomatoes and cover with grated cheese.
Place in microwave or oven until cheese melts.

title: baked pineapple with cheese
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Add grated cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine butter with Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes into thin slices, about 1/8-inch thick.
Place flat on cookie sheet coated with vegetable spray.
Bake for 10 minutes, turn slices over and bake 10 more minutes.
Turn again, bake until brown and crisp.
Remove individual slices as they become crisp.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Wash peppers. Cut a slice from stem end and remove all white pulp and seeds. Mix all other ingredients and place this stuffing into the peppers. Place peppers in baking dish. Add 1 cup HOT water in bottom of dish. Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Note:
Add oil from second jar of artichoke hearts as needed.

title: meat loaf deluxe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole dish; can be divided and frozen and baked layer.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic salt.
Simmer spaghetti sauce and seasoning 45 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles for 8 minutes.
Layer 1/3 meat, 3 noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 meat, 3 noodles, 1/3 meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: Combine 1/3 cup soup with meat, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Shape into 8 oval patties.
Brown patties in skillet. Pour off grease.
Gradually blend remaining soup into flour until smooth.
Add to remaining ingredients; pour over patties.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir sauce occasionally.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Boil shortening, butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture while still hot.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes in a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Melt remaining ingredients except powdered sugar.
Pour over powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Ice cake while both are still warm.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool; crumble into small pieces.
Mix pudding as directed on box; set aside.
Place in large bowl or punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 cake, 1/2 bananas, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1 can pie filling and 1/2 Cool Whip. Repeat again, ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecans.

title: salmon macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Combine celery soup and milk.
Add macaroni, salmon, pimiento and 1/2 cup of grated cheese.
Turn into greased casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut squash into 1/2-inch thick round slices.
Core apples.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Brush apples with lemon juice to prevent browning.
In a 1-quart casserole dish, layer squash and apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon (2 tablespoons of raisins can be added, if desired).
Bake covered at 350° for 50 minutes or until squash is tender.
Before serving, drizzle with the 2 tablespoons syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Divide cake into thirds and crumble 1/3 into bottom of large punch bowl.
Cover with 1/3 cup chocolate syrup, then cover with 1/3 chocolate pudding.
Next, cover with 1/3 Cool Whip.
Add 1/3 crumbled candy bar on top.
Repeat this process 2 more times.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Peel potatoes.
Slice into thin slices. Boil potatoes until done.

title: ranch style bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; toss gently and set aside. Combine mayonnaise and water; beat with a wire whisk until smooth. Pour over chicken mixture; stir well.
Add eggs and toss gently. Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash until tender; mash.
Mix cornbread with milk and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Mix black pepper, soup, poultry seasoning and squash.
Add to celery and onion.
Stir in cornbread mixture.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole dish and bake until set in 350° oven.

title: chicken broccoli vegetable saute
directions: In a skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: bacon stew
directions: Put all in a heavy pot.
Cover with water.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked. Thicken with a little flour.

title: easy stew
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add water and salt to taste. Bring to a boil.
Simmer until potatoes and carrots are done. Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Place chops in an ungreased pan.
Top each chop with 1 slice each of onion and lemon, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes more, basting occasionally, until done.

title: pretzel strawberry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together crushed pretzels, melted margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar; spread in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Add egg.
Mix in flour, salt and baking soda; mix together, then stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
They will look moist and light.
Do not remove from pan for about 2 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Pour smoke over brisket placed in large baking dish; sprinkle with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt on top.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, pour off smoke and sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: summer cake
directions: Mash oranges in own juice; add to cake mix.
Add eggs and oil; mix.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) prepared pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°; let cool.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Wash and core tomatoes.
Peel onions.
Core and seed peppers. Run all through coarse blade of food chopper.
Mix in salt and let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain well, discarding liquid. Tie mixed pickling spices in a cheesecloth bag and add to vegetables and remaining ingredients in an open kettle.
Slowly bring to a simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cook 30 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks and cheesecloth bag and discard. Ladle relish into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 12 pints.

title: sweet and sour radishes
directions: With the flat side of a heavy cleaver, gently crush radishes, being careful not to break them in pieces.
Cut leaves in 1/2-inch sections.
Mix salt with leaves and radishes and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and sesame oil. Pour over radishes.
Serve cold.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each cookie with fork that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, onion and egg.
Gradually beat in milk.
Drop from spoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: fruited cranberry punch
directions: Freeze 2 cups cranberry juice cocktail in ice cube trays. Combine remaining cranberry juice, orange juice, pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar in a large pitcher.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Chill until ready to serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in plastic or glass bowl.
Stir together syrup, sugar, butter and salt and cook at medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook without stirring for five minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda. Pour over popcorn; stir to coat well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 250°.
(Stir with a spoon after 10 minutes.)
Break apart when cool.

title: chopped dipped grapes
directions: In an 8 ounce custard cup melt chocolate and shortening in a saucepan of hot water; stir until smooth.
Dip grape clusters in chocolate to coat to within 1/2 inch from stems.
Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheet or tray.
Chill until chocolate is firm. Makes 30 clusters.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix very well and pour in pie shell.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: quick hot dog chili
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain all fat; then add Manwich and chili.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: stuff and clutter
directions: Heat oven to 150°.
Put in fat, butter and seasonings and add other ingredients.
For the first hour, lift carefully with spatula or pancake turner
every 15 minutes until all the ingredients are well blended.
Bake in slow oven 4 to 6 hours and turn carefully and often in order that the flavor may be well blended through the mixture.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper and onion in margarine.
In another pot cook Lipton onion soup mix, using half the water as directed on the package.
Add 3/4 cup of rice.
While the rice and soup mix is cooking, brown 1 pound of sausage in pan.
Pour off grease and drain on paper towels.
Combine all ingredients in one casserole with the slivered almonds.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in cake pan or an angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling and pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together; stir into lemon gelatin.
Add undrained pineapple.
Whip heavy cream; fold into mixture.
Fold in marshmallows.
Spread lemon mixture over cherry layer and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Set until firm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Tear each tortilla in 8 pieces.
Combine everything except cheese and tortillas in a bowl.
Make layers in baking dish (9 x 13-inch), starting with tortilla:
tortilla, sauce and cheese. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls(unbaked)
directions: Heat brown sugar, syrup and peanut butter to dissolve sugar and blend.
Add coconut and Rice Krispies.
Roll into 1-inch balls. When cold, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 50 to 60 balls.

title: sue crouch's tangy fruit punch
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 40.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown beef with bacon.
Add onions and cook until tender but not brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add seasoning to meat mixture. Stir in soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil. Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange raw beef in single layer in a casserole dish.
Put vegetables in layer on top of meat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle top with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour 1 (8 ounce) can tomato paste and 1 can water on top, then sprinkle 2 tablespoons tapioca on top.
Seal tightly with foil.
Place in 325° oven for 2 hours.
No peeking!

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Put chocolate in double boiler to melt.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy throughout.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition, until sugar is well blended.
Beat until egg whites stand in stiff peaks.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well (entire process takes about 10 minutes).
Fold in chocolate, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.
A nice party cookie.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan (not greased).
Mix cake mix as directed. Set aside.
In pan, layer coconut, pecans and chocolate chips. Pour cake batter over this.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, lemon juice and bananas. Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie(quick and easy)
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for awhile to thicken.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, and salt in mixing bowl with lightly beaten egg whites.
Add pecans and stir until coated.
Sprinkle in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 20 minutes. Remove nuts while warm to cool on waxed paper.

title: icebox pineapple pie
directions: Mix juice into condensed milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix dry ingredients (only 2 tablespoons sugar) and add oleo and cut in.
Press in bottom and part way up sides of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cut 6 peaches in slices and arrange on top.
Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon to balance of sugar and sprinkle over top.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Beat 2 egg yolks and add 1 cup half and half and pour over and bake 20 minutes more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with 1/2 cup pecans and 1/4 cup parsley.
Refrigerate for 1 hour after forming a ball.
Then add rest of pecans and parsley and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and pound with a meat mallet or edge of potato masher. Place in bag with flour and coat well.
Brown on both sides and place in a crock-pot.
Layer meat with sliced onions and mushrooms.
In a skillet, heat mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix.
Blend well and pour over the meat.
Cook on low-medium several hours.
Makes a good gravy.
The flour from the meat helps to thicken it.
This is a Sunday dinner favorite, too.
It cooks while we're in church.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add butter and eggs gradually. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hot toddy
directions: Mugs or short glasses with a teaspoon may be used.
Combine all ingredients except boiling water in a container or shaker. Mix well.
Pour equally into glasses.
Fill glasses to top with boiling water.
Serves 6.

title: one-pan spaghetti
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, brown beef. Drain off excess fat. Add water, sauce mix, tomato paste, butter and salt. Bring to boiling. Add spaghetti. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally until spaghetti is tender, about 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, milk and margarine to dry ingredients, mixing until blended.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Bring 1 3/4 cups water and tea bags to boil.
Remove tea bags and add sugar.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in freezer until slushy.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and whipping cream. Add extracts and flour. Beat egg
whites and fold into mixture. Start in a cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and Miracle Whip well, then spread over baked crescent rolls.
Add vegetables.
Grate cheese on top.
Chill and serve.

title: cereal and peanut cookies(yields 48 cookies)
directions: Mix in saucepan sugar and syrup and bring to a rolling boil; take off of the stove.
Add peanut butter, coconut, cereal and pecans.
Do not bake; drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
You may use crunchy peanut butter and no pecans.
You must work fast after you put the peanut butter in syrup.

title: beef tartare
directions: Cut away all visible fat from ground sirloin.
Grind meat twice.
Add eggs, onion and olive oil.
Mix very well.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Form into mound.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Finely chop cranberries and orange in food chopper.
Stir in sugar.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix strawberries and sugar; set aside. Mix Bisquick baking mix, milk, sugar and melted butter.
Spread in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Cut in pieces.
Split each piece.
Spoon strawberries on bottom layer.
Put top on and add remaining strawberries and whipped cream over top of each piece.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Prepare potato; in a large bowl, sprinkle yeast in warm water. In separate bowl, blend egg and sugar, add potato, milk, butter and salt; add to yeast mixture.
Thoroughly beat in two cups flour. Gradually add remaining flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny (about eight minutes).
Put into lightly greased bowl and cover tightly with plastic wrap; allow to double in bulk (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Cut dough in 16 to 24 pieces for forming.
Set formed rolls on greased baking sheet and allow to rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 400° for 12 to 16 minutes, brush with melted butter.

title: t-j miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables.
Add soup mix.
Cover with water in large pot. Boil for 10 minutes.
Cover and lower heat until vegetables are cooked.
Do not overcook.
T-J Soup can be eaten anytime hunger pangs strike.
It does not add calories to your diet.
The more you eat, the more weight you lose!

title: ham and sweet potato bake(or squash)
directions: Mix potatoes, cream,
rosemary leaves, onion salt and pepper. Place mixture in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Brown ham slice on both sides.
Cut into serving pieces; place over potatoes.
Brush with corn syrup.
Cover casserole with foil.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: never fail pie crust(makes 2 double crusts and 1 or 2 pie shells.)
directions: Measure dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Break egg into a 2-cup measuring cup and beat with a fork.
Add water to level of 1 cup and beat again.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and pour liquid into well.
Mix lightly with a fork, tossing flour from sides until it is all moistened.
Knead.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together as a crust.
Will be crumbly. Put 1/2 of crust mixture in bottom of 2-quart casserole or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Press down.
Place rhubarb on top.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Saute shrimp and onions in sprayed nonstick skillet for 3 to 4 minutes. Add soup and salt and pepper to taste. Heat thoroughly. Serve over pasta. Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: orange toll house cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Rinse chicken but do not dry. Coat chicken with Parmesan and crumbs which have been mixed together. Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Brown chicken approximately 5 minutes on each side; remove to platter. Reduce heat to medium; add broth to skillet and stir to loosen drippings. Remove from heat. Serve over chicken with lemon wedges.

title: lemon tomato aspic salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add vinegar, warmed tomato soup, diced avocado, cucumber, celery and green onions.
Put in mold and chill.

title: english muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and flour.
Mix until blended and dough is soft.
Roll 1/4 inch thick on floured board.
Cut in 3 1/2-inch circles (smaller for cocktail size).
Place on cornmeal sprinkled baking sheet.
Sprinkle more cornmeal on top.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake on medium hot griddle (ungreased) or 350° electric skillet about 7 minutes on each side until browned.
Makes 12 large or 36 small muffins.

title: iroquois indian cornbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time, beating. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin. Do not overbeat, just blend quickly. Add milk and cornmeal then fold in blueberries and nuts. Bake in loaf pan in 350 degree oven, about 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash cooked sweet potatoes; measure 2 cups.
Add other ingredients in order.
Mix with electric mixer until mixture is almost smooth.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: jelly cake
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine milk and vanilla. Add 1/3 of the flour mixture, then half of the milk.
Repeat until all ingredients are added.
Pour into prepared pans and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Spread layers with favorite jam or jelly.

title: vegetable casserole no. 2
directions: Crush crackers
and
put
a layer into a 2 quart casserole. Mix
all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Spread over cracker crumbs.
Put cracker crumbs on top vegetables.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: antipasto roll-ups
directions: Mash together tuna, egg, mayonnaise and lemon juice and set aside.
Cut each cheese slice into 4 pieces.
Arrange a piece of cheese on each slice of salami, trimming cheese to fit.
Spread about one teaspoon of tuna mixture over the cheese.
Roll up and secure with three wooden picks.
Chill.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Precook broccoli according to pkg. directions. Saute onion in butter; add cheese and let melt. Add soups and milk (use soup can to measure milk). Keep stirring to prevent sticking. Add cooked broccoli. Serve with crackers.

title: s.o.s. "chipped beef"
directions: Blend beef in blender until grated.
Brown beef in a little shortening.
Make usual cream gravy in same skillet with beef.

title: philadelphia pound cake
directions: Let all ingredients come to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Gradually add flour and baking powder; mix on low speed until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9x5 in. baking pan or 10 in. tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour and twenty minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool five minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar just before serving if desired.
Serves 10-12.

title: glogg(swedish christmas punch)
directions: Put dried orange peel, cardamon seed, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a cheesecloth bag.
Combine alcohol, brandy, Port, Claret and sugar in a large stock pot or kettle.
Place or suspend cheesecloth bag in pot.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
To reduce evaporation and improve flavor, cover pot with stainless steel bowl to fit, filled with ice.
Serve hot with a few raisins and almonds in each cup.
Best consumed after the Christmas Eve candlelight service.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, chocolate, butter and milk for 1 minute after mixture starts to boil.
Take off at once; add to mixture of oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix in large punch bowl.
Yields 5 quarts or 40 to 50 servings.

title: the queen's quick oats and honey
directions: Boil water and pinch of salt.
Stir in oats (occasionally); cook about 3 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in honey for 1 minute.
Turn off heat; cover and let sit for 1 minute.
Pour in bowl.
Add milk.
Eat and enjoy.

title: chili sauce
directions: Skin and chop tomatoes; place in large pot.
Finely chop onions, green peppers, hot peppers and celery.
Add to tomatoes. Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Tie allspice, cinnamon sticks, cloves, paprika and celery seed in a cheesecloth bag.
Heat mixture to boiling; lower heat and simmer for several hours, until desired thickness.
As mixture thickens, stir.

title: pult or klub
directions: Add all ingredients together, mixing well.
Fill cloths (or aluminum foil) and place a strip of salt pork or leaf lard in center.
Wrap in a long roll.
Cook for 2 hours in boiling water. Slice and fry.
Serve with butter and sugar.

title: lamb stew
directions: Add together flour, salt and pepper to make seasoned flour. Cook rice; keep hot.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until lightly brown.
Add lamb and liquid season.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken with flour mixture.
Place cubed lamb in brown paper bag with seasoned flour.
Shake until lamb is evenly coated. Heat salad oil in a heavy skillet.
Brown lamb well on all sides. Add onions and garlic and cook until golden.
Add celery seed, rosemary and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrot and onion.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over mashed potatoes or dumplings.

title: hashbrown potatoes casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine potatoes, soup, onions, 1/2 c. melted butter, sour cream and cheese. Place in a 9-inch x 13-inch casserole dish. top with cornflakes and drizzle with remaining melted butter. Cover with foil and bake on middle rack for 40 minutes. remove foil and bake an additional 20 minutes. Yields 10-12 servings.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Place unbrowned chops in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chops. Cover tightly with foil. Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: barbecue oysters
directions: Place oysters in barbecue until they pop open.
Pry apart and loosen oyster.
Try to keep as much liquid as possible in deep shell.
Squeeze lemon juice, 1 tablespoon sauce and 1 tablespoon cheese on top of oyster.
Return to the barbecue until heated. Plan on 2 to 4 oysters per person.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and juices.
Freeze in containers.
Add ginger ale when ready to use.

title: israeli carrots
directions: Combine garlic, salt, pepper, lemon juice and olive oil with 2 tablespoons parsley.
Toss with carrots to mix well.
Pour onto serving plate and sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes and onion.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion over potatoes to hot oil.
Brown, but do not burn.
Reduce heat to low and cover skillet.
Cook approximately 10 minutes.
Remove lid and return heat to high.
Cook 1 or 2 more minutes.
Drain on paper towels before serving.
Serves 2.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Mix together.
Press into pan.
