title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together salad dressing, vinegar, garlic and salad seasonings.
Pour over pasta.
Mix well.
Add veggies; marinate overnight.
Adding diced cheese is extra nice too.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight. Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoon of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar; shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken and pasta toss(a salad)
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse under cold running water; drain.
Combine pasta, spinach, chicken, tomatoes, mushrooms and cheese in a medium salad bowl.
Whisk together oil, mustard, lemon juice, garlic salt, 3 tablespoons water and 1/8 teaspoon pepper until smooth.
Pour over pasta mixture; toss lightly.
Serve immediately with hot French bread. Serves 4.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and chili powder. Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in whole tomatoes and beef bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickens and bubbles, 1 minute.
Add tomato and chili with beans (or cook your own pinto beans).
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 15 minutes or until thick.
Cook flour tortillas flat in boiling water, according to label.
Lay each tortilla flat and sprinkle with 1/4 cup grated cheese and 1 tablespoon onion.
Roll up and place seam side down in a greased baking dish.
Pour chili sauce over and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: ukranian winter borscht
directions: Melt butter in pot over moderate heat.
When foam subsides, add onion and garlic and saute about 5 minutes, then add carrots and saute 2 minutes.
Add turnip, parsnip and celeriac and saute 5 minutes more.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar. Saute 2 more minutes.
Stir to combine and bring to a boil, then simmer at lower heat 15 minutes.
In saucepan, bring 2 quarts beef stock to boil.
Add cabbage and potatoes.
Return to boil.
Simmer and cook 5 minutes.
Transfer cabbage, potatoes and beet stock to mixture.
Stir in parsley, 1/3 cup dill and shredded beet.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into cracker crusts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in 1 cup of warm water for 20 minutes.
Cream together 1 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and orange juice.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Drain and stir in apricots.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain and cool carrots, don't overcook.
Mix onion and pepper with carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots and marinate for at least 12 hours before serving.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook until berries burst open.
Mix gelatine with 1/2 cup water and add to cranberry mixture.
Let cool.
Add nuts, apples and pineapple. Pour into a serving dish.
Chill.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain.
Stir milk into soup.
Add chicken, half the cheese, the mushrooms, pimiento and macaroni; mix well.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Uncover and stir.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 2 to 3 minutes more or until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix egg, milk and vanilla.
Combine with flour and mix well.
Chill for about 1 hour, then roll out and cut.
Cook in a 250° oven.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, oleo and sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes and let cool.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Over the mixture, spread the pizza sauce and the green and red pepper.
Sprinkle the cheese over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Dip for chips, Doritos, etc.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Brown meat in large skillet over medium high heat, drain. Stir in taco seasoning, tomato sauce and corn. Simmer 5 minutes. Spoon mixture into a 2 qt. baking dish. Top with cheese and tortilla chips and bake until cheese melts (5-10 minutes).

title: my grandmother's molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add butter, egg and molasses. Sift together the flour and spices.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter and sugar mixture.
Roll in small balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pagoda beans
directions: Take 1/2 cup liquid from beans and heat in a large saucepan. Add 2 bouillon cubes, 1/4 teaspoon ginger and butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Add water chestnuts, onions and mushrooms.
Heat until hot and add a mixture of 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Add beans and heat until hot and serve.

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, garlic salt and cumin.
In another bowl, beat egg, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips together until smooth.
Stir in Crispix cereal.
Put mixture in paper bag along with 3 cups of powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Pour berries into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with flour mixture and lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Place 2nd pie shell over, seal edges and cut holes on top.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake or texas hot chocolate cake
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, mix together butter, cocoa, water and buttermilk.
Bring to rapid boil.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans to boiling and drain.
Pour beans in large casserole dish.
Put onion on top.
Add celery soup.
Add cheese. Melt butter and add to cracker crumbs.
Put crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes about 1 gallon.
Can be stored in refrigerator for months.
Good on chicken or pork.

title: mattie's slaw dressing
directions: Add mustard to sugar and vinegar; heat until sugar dissolves. Beat eggs and pour first mixture into this and cook until thick. Add butter when taken from stove.
Pour dressing over cabbage and mix.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently and chill.
Just before serving, add cashews, if desired.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Serves 6.

title: butter fancies
directions: Beat together the softened butter, milk, vanilla and 1 cup of the sugar in a medium size bowl until smooth.
Slowly beat in 1 additional cup sifted 10x sugar until frosting is good spreading consistency.
Beat in several drops of food coloring to tint, if you wish.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: mock baby ruth bars or carolina crunchy bars
directions: Mix and press down into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and sliced bananas with the drained pineapple.
Finally, add the chopped walnuts.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Flatten chicken pieces between sheets of wax paper with rolling pin or mallet.
Pieces should be 1/4-inch thick.
Combine egg and milk in dish.
Combine flour, salt and pepper on wax paper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then into flour mixture to coat all sides.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet. Brown chicken on both sides.
Remove to platter.
Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic until tender.
Remove to platter.
Add wine and chicken broth to pan; boil 10 minutes to reduce liquid.
Return chicken and vegetables to pan; heat thoroughly.
Arrange on platter.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: tin can ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1-pound coffee can with a tight fitting plastic lid.
Place lid on can.
Place can with ingredients inside a 3-pound can with a tight fitting plastic lid. Pack larger can with crushed ice around smaller can.
Pour at least 3/4 c. rock salt evenly over ice.
Place lid on 3-pound can. Have 2 children roll can back and forth on a table or cement slab for 10 minutes.
Open outer can; remove inner can with ingredients.
Use a rubber spatula to stir mixture.
Scrape sides of can; replace lid.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugars, eggs and salt.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add oats, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: taco cornbread
directions: Brown the following: ground chuck, onion and bell pepper. Add taco seasoning. Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture into prepared skillet. Pour ground beef mixture in center and spread to edges. Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Cover completely with remaining cornbread mixture. Bake until set. Serve with dollop of sour cream if desired.

title: mocha espresso
directions: Combine coffee, sugar, dry milk and cocoa; mix well.
Store mix in airtight container.
For each serving, place 1/4 cup of mix in cup and add 1 cup boiling water; stir well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon brandy flavoring.
Garnish with whipped cream and grated chocolate, if desired.
Yields 18 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Warm refried beans.
Cut flour tortillas to fit.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer tortillas, beans, sauce and cheese.
Repeat; will be 3 layers. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.
Cut into squares.
Top with sour cream and salsa.

title: macaroni and cheese(club member: nicholas)
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Combine all other ingredients, except milk and cracker crumbs, together; mix with macaroni. Save some cheese for top. Pour milk around and over ingredients. Top with cheese and cracker crumbs; cover. Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: low-fat pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spray pan with Pam and cook to desired doneness.
More milk may be added for thinner pancake batter.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Melt coating in saucepan.
Spread peanut butter between crackers.
Dip in coating and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until done; drain and place in buttered casserole.
Cut up cheese and put over vegetables.
Mix melted margarine and crackers and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix first four foods.
Form cone shaped; dip into cracker crumbs.
Cook 5 minutes on each side.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot several hours or bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rosemary and garlic pizza bread
directions: Mix water with flours, yeast, 2 tablespoons olive oil and salt.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to bowl and let double. Press dough into 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Brush with rest of olive oil.
Sprinkle garlic, crushed rosemary, kosher salt and crushed peppercorns.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Brush with additional olive oil if desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease dish and put chicken bits on bottom.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour mixture over chicken. Stir together stuffing and melted butter.
Put this on top of dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add next 6 ingredients and small amount of Mozzarella cheese.
Add 1/2 of Ragu sauce and stir together.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll rolls; place in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, pinching edges together to seal.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool completely. Combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; beat until well blended.
Spread mixture over crust; sprinkle with cheese and veggies.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch bites.
(Yields about 8 dozen.)

title: chicken taquitos
directions: Simmer chicken in 10-inch skillet 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Shred chicken.
Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil 1 to 3 minutes.
Mix ingredients and saute 3 to 5 minutes.
In large skillet, heat 3 to 4 cups oil.
Fill, fold tortillas and fry.

title: fresh apple spice cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and spices together with a fork.
In another bowl, mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt to the apple mixture, then add eggs mixture.
Fold in raisins. Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer until well blended.
Great to freeze in butter cups and thaw as needed.

title: low-fat enchiladas(no meat, bean filled)
directions: To make sauce, heat oil, chili powder and flour in a small saucepan to make a paste.
Add water gradually; stir in vinegar, garlic powder, onion powder, salt and oregano.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer 3 minutes.

title: june birthday cake
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar.
Add water and flour alternately to creamed mixture.
Add flavorings and mix well. Beat egg whites stiff and add 1 cup sugar to blend well.
Fold egg whites in last until well blended.
Do not beat as it destroys lightness of egg whites.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Have oven fairly hot the first 5 minutes, then reduce heat and bake remaining 15 minutes.

title: eggplant and angel hair pasta
directions: In a large heavy pot, saute over high fire the garlic, onions and celery until slightly wilted.
Then add eggplant and reduce heat to medium.
Cover pot and allow the eggplant to smother. Stir occasionally.
When eggplant is very tender, add the chicken broth, tasso and tomatoes.
Cover pot again and simmer for 1 hour, stirring from time to time.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes. Check for seasonings.
If tasso is highly seasoned, no other seasonings may be needed.
To cook angel hair pasta, I give this tip.
Bring 8 cups water seasoned with 1 teaspoon salt to boil in large pot.
Add 12 ounces pasta.
Turn off the fire.
Cover and let stand 6 minutes.
Drain.
Pour cool water over the pasta and allow to drain well.
Toss with a couple of tablespoons olive oil. Toss the pasta with the eggplant mixture and garnish with freshly grated Romano cheese.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Place tomato soup and Worcestershire in saucepan and bring to simmer.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of water and add to saucepan. Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and mix with hand mixer until smooth.
Add onion, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Pour into a greased 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with mini rye or other mini breads.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and walnuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing and garnish with apple slices before serving, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put roast in crock-pot	with
soup and add onion.
Salt and pepper the roast, then
add
enough
water to cover top of roast. Turn crock-pot on low and cook all day.

title: spaetzle
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Add eggs and milk; stir to mix well (batter will be thick).

title: pico de gallo
directions: Stir together all the ingredients in a medium size bowl. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fresh veggie pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing together with a little milk.
Spread crescent rolls along bottom of pizza pan. Add the ingredients, using your imagination on the veggies.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: glazed orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift together flour and salt.
In a medium bowl, combine candy, dates, walnuts and coconut.
Mix well. Add 1/2 cup flour to mixture. Toss to coat evenly. Set aside. In a large bowl, cream the margarine.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine baking soda and buttermilk.
Mix well. Add alternately with remaining flour to egg mixture. Add floured candy mixture.
Mix well. Spoon into a greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until done. Remove from oven.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix cocoa, about 3 teaspoons sugar and enough water to make a syrup.
Add rest of ingredients, except sweet milk and mix well. Pour into ice cream can.
Add sweet milk to fill line.
Stir well. Makes 1 gallon.

title: corn stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix corn with liquid, bread crumbs, onions and sage. Stuff pork chop pockets with corn mixture. Fry pork chops in shortening until brown, about 15 minutes. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until pork chops are done, about 1 hour.

title: coffee cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients well.
Spread crescent rolls with points pointed outward.
Fill in center of crescent rolls.
Braid roll ends over filling.
Beat egg whites slightly and brush on rolls.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add brown sugar.
Cool.
Add egg. Sift together dry ingredients and add to sugar and butter.
Stir in vanilla; mix.
Add pecans.
Spread in 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add flour and mix well until smooth.
Then add milk.
Keep stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Then add a large jar of Cheez Whiz.
Stir until melted.
Add a little salt and pepper to taste.
Take drained macaroni and put in a baking dish.
Pour in cheese sauce and mix well.
Place slices of cheese on top of macaroni mixture and bake at 350° until cheese is light brown and bubbly.
Delicious!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, flour and eggs; set aside.
Cube bread and melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix bread and butter; spread over pineapple that has been put in a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes, or until bread is medium toasted.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple and pecans.
Fold in ice cream.
Refrigerate.

title: monterey green beans
directions: In a saucepan, saut onions in butter until tender.
Add beans, mushrooms, lemon pepper and salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until beans are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand for 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Prepare crust and set aside.
In small saucepan, soften gelatin in cold water.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves completely.
Stir into yogurt.
Mash strawberries and fold into the yogurt.
Stir in Equal.
Pour into the graham cracker crust.
When pie is firm, whip dessert topping and spread on top of pie.
Chill. Serves 8. Contains 135 calories per serving.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and lemon peel.
Beat until well mixed.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Wrap and chill dough.

title: pizza mac
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine milk and egg.
Add to macaroni.
Mix and pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Top with hamburger, pepperoni, onion, mushrooms, green pepper and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares to serve.
Very good one meal dish!!

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Put vinegar, water and salt in pot and bring to a rolling boil.
Cold pack pickles and pour solution over them.
Seal. Makes 6 or 7 jars.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken seasoned with salt, pepper and celery. Remove from bones.
Reserve 1 1/2 quarts broth. Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo. Boil package of vermicelli in broth.
Do not drain. To this, add the peas (drained) and mushrooms (drained). Cut cheese into small pieces and add this, Ro-Tel (juice optional), onion and pepper with chicken.
Mix carefully.
Put in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend flour into cottage cheese.
Add eggs, beating well. Stir
in milk, corn, onion and seasonings.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs. Bake, covered, at 225° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients except cocoa.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture along with vanilla.
Batter is thin.
Grease and flour 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cover cabbage, celery and onions with water.
Boil down until ingredients are barely covered with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes in a large casserole, covered, or a large baking dish, 14 x 9-inch, covered with foil.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Pat and spread rolls into cookie sheet.
Prick with fork. Bake and cool.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing; spread on cooled crust.
Place vegetables on top.
Add cheese. Refrigerate, then cut into squares.

title: louisiana  banana nut cake(an old-time favorite from my mother's kitchen)
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar together in a large mixer bowl, then add the shortening, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Add the bananas, eggs and nuts.
Beat another 4 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer first six ingredients (in order listed) in a plastic 9 x 13 pan with a tight fitting lid. Combine mayonnaise and sugar. Spread over the salad.
Top with grated cheddar cheese.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator eight to ten hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach, drain well.
Saute onions in butter; mix.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese into casserole.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top.
Crumble crisp bacon over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Boil whole chicken in chicken bouillon cubes until done.
Take from water and remove all bones from the meat.
Add 2 packages Reames frozen egg noodles (in freezer section at store).
Add any vegetables you want and the chicken.
Return pan to boil, then down to simmer and continue cooking until veggies and noodles are done.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread on sliced rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and boil for 1 minute, then cool.
While cooling, chop vegetables.
Sprinkle salt over vegetable mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Pour the cool liquid over the vegetable mixture and place in jars or containers.
Can be eaten at once or is delicious frozen before serving.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Take meatball size portion of dough, roll into long strip and twist into a pretzel shape. Continue this method until dough is used up.

title: salsa dip
directions: Pour salsa over cream cheese and top with shrimp.
Serve with taco chips.
Nice last minute entry for a potluck.

title: hanky panks
directions: Saute sausage and beef; drain well.
Add cheese and melt over low heat.
Add spices.
Spread on rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet to freeze.
After frozen, place in freezer bag.
When ready to use, take out of freezer and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 35 to 40.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch dish, mix soups and milk.
Add Veg All, broccoli, chicken, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Microwave on high for 10 to 15 minutes until hot.
Place pie crust on top.
Prick crust in several places with a fork to vent.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes until crust is light brown.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Put in double boiler.
Boil until thick; add juice of 1 can pineapple.
Remove from stove.
Add crushed pineapple.
Put layer of graham crackers (not rolled) and layer of pudding until used.
Use egg whites for meringue on top.

title: corn chowder
directions: Preheat a large, heavy saucepan over medium heat for about 1 minute.
Spray it twice with oil.
Saute onion for 5 minutes or until translucent.
Add 4 cups corn and saute for 4 to 5 minutes, until it softens a bit.
Add 2 cups broth and cook 20 minutes or until corn is tender.
Pour into blender and puree until smooth. Return puree to saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add bell pepper, rosemary, thyme, black pepper, ground red pepper and the remaining 1 cup chicken broth and 2 cups corn.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes more, until thick and creamy.
Serves 4.

title: creole corn chowder
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, saute bacon until crisp.
Add onion and peppers.
Cook until limp.
Add ham, corn, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Make a roux of flour and oil. Add roux to corn mixture.
Bring milk to boil.
Add milk to corn mixture.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, add cream; heat.

title: tiramisu
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir well with whisk. Cover surface with plastic wrap. Chill 30 minutes or until firm. Remove plastic wrap and add cream cheese. Beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended. Gently fold in whipped topping. Combine hot water, Kahlua and Espresso. Split ladyfingers.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Cream the dry pudding and cream cheese together, then add fruit cocktail.
Beat with mixer so that fruit will be chopped up into small pieces.
Shape into ball.
Cover with crushed pecans. Serve on cinnamon graham crackers.

title: sour cream potato toss
directions: Combine the potatoes, cucumber, onion, salt, celery seed and pepper. Sieve egg yolks; set aside.
Chop egg whites.
Add to potato mixture. Chill.
Blend together the egg yolks, sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard. Pour over potato mixture. Toss and chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine or spread in a large microwavable bowl on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine or spread.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring about 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Using greased spatula or wax paper, press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well the shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix flour and salt.
Stir in.
Roll 1 teaspoon dough into balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place on baking sheet and press thumb into center of each.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Fill cooked thumbprints with tinted confectioners frosting or candied fruit.

title: pico de gallo
directions: May substitute 2 tablespoons chopped parsley for cilantro and basil.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into balls; mash slightly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°. Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: uniquely yours "chicken" casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix together celery, onions, mushrooms and rice.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
rice, chicken, sauce, cheese and breadcrumbs or sliced almonds.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 5/8-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool 3 hours.

title: chocolate-praline pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on low heat for at least 2 hours. Stir often.
If you desire a very hot relish, add more pepper. Can according to canning directions.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in tomato juice.
Mix all ingredients, except the last 2. Cover with a mixer of the catsup and brown sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Sift flour, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon and add.
Add nut meats (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coleslaw souffle salad
directions: Pour hot water over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add water, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt.
Beat until well blended. Chill until slightly firm.
Beat with egg beater until fluffy. Fold in cabbage, onion and celery seed.
Pour into 1 quart mold. Refrigerate until firm.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt over low heat or microwave the chips and peanut butter. Add peanuts.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: "you won't believe" toffee crunch cookies
directions: Place saltines in one layer on large cookie sheet.
Melt margarine and sugar in saucepan or microwave.
Stir to mix them; immediately pour over crackers, coating all.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until bubbly.
Turn off oven.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Return to warm oven for 2 minutes to soften chips.
Spread with knife and sprinkle on nuts if desired. Cut before too cold or they break.
If this happens, pop back into oven for a coup more minutes.
Great!

title: squash cheese casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash in salt water until tender.
Drain and mash well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: espresso chocolate cheese cake
directions: Let the cream cheese soften to room temperature.
In a large bowl, blend crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter in a medium bowl.
Press firmly over the bottom and halfway up the side of a lightly buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill before filling. Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Dissolve Espresso in 2 tablespoons hot water.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish for 40 minutes at 325°.
This recipe will serve 7 people.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While hot, roll gently in powdered sugar.

title: homemade apple turnover
directions: Thaw puff pastry for 30 minutes at room temperature. Mix egg and water for egg wash. Unfold pastries. On lightly floured surface, and spoon half the apple mixture down the middle of each pastry. Fold sides of pastry over the top of the apples. Close ends by making a half fold at each end and use a stiff pastry brush dipped in the egg wash to adhere. Brush egg wash covering pastries. Make 3 diagonal cuts across of tops of turnovers. Transfer to large baking sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown. Cool for 15 minutes. Spoon frosting into ziploc bag, zip it up and cut a small corner off bottom of bag. Drizzle lines of frosting over top of turnovers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and slice carrots 1/4-inch thick.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain; add onion, pepper and celery.
Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf as a salad or use as relish or pickle.
Keeps 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: crisco cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, adding one egg at a time.
Add milk and flour, a little at a time.
The secret to this cake rising is the beating.
Beat, beat, beat.
Bake in tube pan for 2 hours at 350°.

title: weight watchers cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients together except nuts.
Form into a ball or log.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.
Serve with fat-free crackers. Serves 16 generous servings.
Each:
1/4 P, 1/2 Fat and 40 opt. cal.
If using fat-free cheese, each is 1/4 P, 1/4 Fat and 50 opt. cal.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan.
Gradually add water, stirring until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually add 1/4 of hot mixture into remaining hot mixture.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon rind and juice, stirring until butter melts.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar until foamy. Gradually add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over warm filling, sealing to edge of pastry. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool to room temperature.

title: harvest fruit compote (for grilling)(serving size: 8)
directions: Arrange fruit in an oiled foil pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Fold heavy-duty foil tightly around pan.
Grill over moderately hot coals for 15 minutes or until fruit is hot.

title: west indian pork
directions: Slice tenderloin into 1-inch pieces.
Flatten slightly with heel of hand.
Heat one teaspoon Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add meat.
Brown quickly on both sides, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove meat from skillet.
Keep warm.
Heat remaining 2 teaspoons Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in skillet.
Add bananas.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add brown sugar and brandy.
Cook and stir until sauce is thick and bubbly. Return meat to skillet.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 355 calories, fat 9 g (83 cal or 23% of total calories), sat fat 2 g (6% of total calories), carb 32 g, protein 33 g, chol 105 mg and sodium 85 mg.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend all together except Cool Whip.
Then fold in Cool Whip last.

title: vegetable bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute onions, carrots and celery over medium heat until onion is soft, about 8 minutes.
Stir in water, bouillon, tomatoes, beans, barley, garlic powder and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add spinach; cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Yields 14 servings.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Delicious!

title: spicy cheddar cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a food processor until smooth. Transfer to serving container.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Refrigerate, covered.
Serve with thick bread sticks, pretzel rods or hearty crackers.

title: coconut pecan blondies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg and brown sugar for 3 minutes. Add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to the brown sugar mixture, beating just until blended.
Stir in pecans, coconut and white chocolate.
Spread into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Don't overbake.)
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine ingredients, adding the flour last.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo (or butter) and sugar; beat until smooth. Add egg yolks; beat.
Combine flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites that have been beaten until stiff.
Pour in 3 layer cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pasadena noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Combine with noodles.
Place in buttered casserole, covered, in 300° oven.
Bake 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Drain artichokes.
Place in greased 9 x 13 dish.
Layer rice and chicken over artichokes. Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and 3/4 of cheese together.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Toast bread crumbs in melted butter, toss with parmesan cheese and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 350 for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage; let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add pepper and carrot.
Boil vinegar, water, sugar and spices for about 1 minute.
Cool; pour over slaw.
Package and freeze.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine butter, cheese, salt and pepper with hot drained macaroni in bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Beat eggs and milk in small bowl until well mixed.
Pour over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until macaroni is set and golden brown on top.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Cut a lengthwise slit down the center of each tenderloin to within 1/2-inch of bottom; open tenderloins so they lie flat. Cover with plastic wrap; pound to flatten to 3/4-inch thickness. Remove plastic wrap.
In a large, resealable, plastic bag, combine the oil, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Add tenderloins.
Seal bag and turn to coat.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: people chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Stir to mix; add peanuts and raisins.
Stir to coat.
In large bowl, pour cereal, add chocolate mixture and stir to coat.
In large brown grocery bag, pour one box powdered sugar, then add Crispix cereal mixture and shake until all is coated.
This makes a lot and is real good.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs.
Beat after each addition. Add 3 cups flour (beat on low). Alternate with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
In another bowl, mix the baking soda and cocoa.
Add the warm water. Add vanilla to batter on low. Bake in 3 large layers at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour pie filling into greased 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Cut butter into 12 squares and put on nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces and place in a roasting pan. Slice onions over the ribs (makes two layers).
Combine remaining ingredients to make a sauce.
Mix thoroughly and pour over the onions and ribs.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Uncover last 1/2 hour so ribs will brown.
Easy and good.

title: cheese log
directions: Let cheese set at room temperature until soft. Mix with grated cheese, a few dashes of Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and mayonnaise, if needed, to make a pliable mix, onions, chopped ham, garlic, chopped ripe olives, chopped pimento, crushed pineapple or add your own choices. Form the mix into 2 logs or balls and roll in finely chopped pecans or paprika.
It is better to let set in refrigerator overnight to let flavors blend. Serve at room temperature with a variety of crackers.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruit. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: embutido
directions: You will need plastic wrap and aluminum foil cut into 10 x 12-inch pieces.

title: sweet tomato relish
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bring to the boiling point and cook slowly 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove the spice bag. Makes 4 pints.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add 3 3/4 c. flour; mix well.
Sprinkle a board with some of the remaining flour.
Knead for 5 minutes, add enough remaining flour to make a soft, non-sticky dough.
Roll to 1/2 inch thickness.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Mix enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out.
Bake at 350°.
